    description:
      '\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003ch4\u003e\r\n        Application closes on\r\n    \u003c/h4\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            \u003ctime datetime="2019-06-23T12:00:00Z"\u003e\r\n                23.6.2019\r\n            \u003c/time\u003e\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003ch4\u003e\r\n        Place\r\n    \u003c/h4\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            Department of Computer Science\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003ch4\u003e\r\n        Position\r\n    \u003c/h4\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            Teaching and research positions\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We have funded research positions available for students in the computer\r\n    vision research group led by Prof. Juho Kannala at Aalto University.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The research carried out in the position will aim at applying deep\r\n    reinforcement learning algorithms for autonomous driving on DonkeyCar, an\r\n    open source DIY self driving platform for small scale cars. This involves:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Setting up the DonkeyCar platform for research.\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Reproducing existing deep reinforcement learning approaches on the\r\n        platform.\r\n        \u003cul\u003e\r\n            \u003cli\u003e\r\n                Eg: Deep Q Networks, Soft Actor-Critic.\r\n            \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Implementing and exploring model-based reinforcement learning\r\n        algorithms.\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The instructors of the work will be Prof. Juho Kannala (\r\n    \u003ca href="https://users.aalto.fi/~kannalj1/"\u003e\r\n        https://users.aalto.fi/~kannalj1/\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    ) and Rinu Boney (\r\n    \u003ca href="https://users.aalto.fi/~boneyr1/"\u003e\r\n        https://users.aalto.fi/~boneyr1/\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    ).\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Requirements\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Strong programming skills (in Python)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Experience with PyTorch/TensorFlow\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Experience with deep learning\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Solid mathematical background\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Previous experience in deep reinforcement learning is beneficial but not\r\n    required.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Application Instructions\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    If you are interested in joining our group, please submit your complete\r\n    application (cover letter, CV and transcript of university courses) via the\r\n    link below by June 23, 2019. The review of applications will be done on a\r\n    rolling basis, so early submissions are strongly encouraged.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    For further information, please visit\r\n    \u003ca href="https://users.aalto.fi/~kannalj1/"\u003e\r\n        https://users.aalto.fi/~kannalj1/\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    or contact Prof. Juho Kannala (juho.kannala@aalto.fi, Tel: +358503537744).\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
