    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Tuxera is looking for an exceptional software engineer who has the passion for solving challenging problems in cutting-edge file system technologies.\r\n    Tuxera designs NTFS, exFAT, FAT, HFS+ and other file systems for Linux, Android, Mac OS X, Windows Embedded, QNX, Nucleus, VxWorks and other popular\r\n    operating systems.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You will participate in the design and implementation of brand name mobile phones, car entertainment systems, set-top boxes and storage products, which are\r\n    empowered by Tuxera file systems. The code you write will run on millions of electronics devices every day.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The candidate is a hardworking software engineer who has a genuine passion for results and can achieve them both independently and as a member of a\r\n    geographically distributed development team. You can take leadership for developing new file system features for robust, scalable, high-performance\r\n    systems.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003ch4\u003e\r\n    Responsibilities:\r\n\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eWork on the design, implementation and support of Tuxera\'s file system technologies\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eProblem and performance analysis and debugging\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eWork with the development team to support customers with their upcoming products\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003ch4\u003e\r\n    Required Experience:\r\n\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eExpert in C and Assembly programming languages\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eExpert in Linux kernel development (VFS, MM, block layer, debugging, profiling, etc.)\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eKnowledge of file systems and operating systems kernel internals\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eProven ability to work on a fast-paced and diverse development environment\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003ch4\u003e\r\n    Preferred Experience:\r\n\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eNTFS, FAT, exFAT, HFS+ or other file systems\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eAndroid, Mac OS X, Windows Embedded, QNX, Nucleus or other Operating Systems\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eEmbedded development\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eBSc or MSc in Computer Science or equivalent skills\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003ch4\u003e\r\n    Benefits:\r\n\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eDynamic work environment, with flexible working hours.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eLaptop, smartphone, health insurance, lunch coupons, and more.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003ch4\u003e\r\n    How to apply:\r\n\u003c/h4\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    This position is full-time and located at Tuxera headquarters in Ruoholahti, Helsinki, Finland. The position will be filled once a suitable candidate is found. Apply at the \u003ca target="_blank" href="http://www.tuxera.com/company/careers/job-application/?aguid=E7C66CBCE69B4679B129AC4B221342BA"\u003eTuxera website\u003c/a\u003e. Please send us your CV and some sample source code that shows your skills.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
