    description:
      '\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003e\r\n        By joining IQM, you will enter a deeptech company set up to drive\r\n        fundamental advancements in quantum computing technology. We are a\r\n        world-class team of quantum physicists, engineers, and software experts\r\n        working together to create new value for quantum computing. IQM is\r\n        integrated into the high-tech campus in Otaniemi near Helsinki,\r\n        providing a state-of-the-art cleanroom and perfect lab conditions.\r\n        Working in the metropolitan area means enjoying the modern Nordic\r\n        lifestyle in one of the most attractive and the happiest countries in\r\n        the world. We have strong ties to other European quantum efforts and\r\n        our international team is connected to business leaders and high-tech\r\n        companies around the globe. Together, we aim to shape the future by\r\n        developing disruptive technologies for quantum computing.\r\n    \u003c/em\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    IQM is now looking for a (Jr.) Software Engineer to a focused,\r\n    collaborative startup environment to support the development of quantum\r\n    computing – do you want to be part of this? IQM, a growing startup company\r\n    with more than 20 professionals, builds scalable hardware for universal\r\n    quantum computers, focusing on superconducting technology addressing the\r\n    next big challenge: scalability. They are developing 2nd generation quantum\r\n    processors based on proprietary technology that allows them to\r\n    significantly speed up the clock speed of quantum processors. Quantum\r\n    computing will revolutionize industries like drug discovery, materials\r\n    science, and finance by solving complex problems in hours instead of years,\r\n    and as the largest quantum computing hardware company in Europe, IQM aims\r\n    to demonstrate the fastest qubit reset and readout in the industry.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cstrong\u003eWe hope you have:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Studies from a relevant technical field\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Independent programming skills with Python\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Some previous work experience from software development (e.g. summer\r\n        internships) – we are also open for experienced developers\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Interest towards the field of quantum computing\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Strong teamwork skills\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Professional skills in English\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eBonus points:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cul\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Previous experience from software testing and test automation\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Knowledge or experience from any other programming languages\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Knowledge or experience from databases (e.g. SQL, No-SQL)\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eSkill tags: Python, SQL\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eRead more and apply by the 17th of November: \u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003ca\r\n        href="https://atalent.fi/open-position/jr-software-engineer"\r\n        target="_blank"\r\n    \u003e\r\n        https://atalent.fi/\r\n        \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n            open-position/jr-software-\r\n            \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n                engineer\r\n            \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n        \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv id=":nh" tabindex="0"\u003e\r\n        \u003cimg src="https://ssl.gstatic.com/ui/v1/icons/mail/images/cleardot.gif"/\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n',
