    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href="http://reaktor.com/careers/spacecraft-software-engineer/" target="blank_"\u003ehttp://reaktor.com/careers/spacecraft-software-engineer/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eReaktor is launching the first Finnish commercial satellite in 2016. Now we’re looking for a Spacecraft Software Engineer trainee to take part in developing software for our satellite and the supporting ground systems. This paid part-time position is optimally suited for students currently majoring in Computer Science (or similar field). Work packages can be scheduled flexibly based on project requirements and trainees’ individual schedule. And when the project ends we hope you can join us full-time.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eThe ideal candidate is someone who already has some experience with programming languages such as Rust, C, C++, Go, Python or Javascript. Knowledge of working with digital signal processing, embedded devices or radio technologies is a definite plus. And even though the actual satellite itself will be far above the troposphere, we do use cloud servers extensively for data processing. You’ll be working with the core satellite team, which is augmented by 350 experienced professionals who are eager to help you with whatever challenges you may come across.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eWe’re also accepting applications from full-time applicants. While we cannot guarantee a full-time placement as a Spacecraft Software Engineer, we have plenty of opportunities for all willing Reaktor employees to make their contribution to this exciting venture. To apply for this once-in-a-lifetime opportunity, either fill the form below or send your application to \u003ca href="mailto:careers@reaktor.com"\u003ecareers@reaktor.com\u003c/a\u003e. Don’t forget to include samples of your coding skills. We’re looking forward to hearing from you!\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eApplications are naturally welcome in Finnish as well!\u003c/p\u003e  ',
