    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Wihuri Research Institute (\r\n    \u003ca href="http://www.wri.fi/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"\u003e\r\n        www.wri.fi\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    ) is a private research institute focusing on cardiovascular diseases,\r\n    located at Meilahti campus. The atherosclerosis research laboratory is now\r\n    seeking a M.Sc student / trainee to work on computational data analysis in\r\n    a project funded by the Academy of Finland. We have developed a method to\r\n    assess person-to-person differences in the quality of low density\r\n    lipoprotein (LDL) particles. The method is based on analysing the\r\n    aggregation susceptibility of isolated LDL particles. We recently showed\r\n    that differences in LDL aggregation are associated with cardiovascular\r\n    deaths (\r\n    \u003ca\r\n        href="https://academic.oup.com/eurheartj/article/39/27/2562/5049093"\r\n        target="_blank"\r\n        rel="noopener noreferrer"\r\n    \u003e\r\n        https://academic.oup.com/eurheartj/article/39/27/2562/5049093\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    ). In the future, we want to evaluate the potential of our method in\r\n    prediction and treatment of cardiovascular diseases.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We are now looking for a trainee / M.Sc. student with a background in a\r\n    quantitative field such as bioinformatics, statistics, data science or\r\n    computer science and a genuine interest to apply her/his skills to\r\n    medically important questions. The trainee/student would be responsible for\r\n    integration of data obtained from (lipid)omic and genome-wide genetic\r\n    analysis with data obtained from LDL analyses and would get supervision\r\n    from experts from both medical and computational sciences.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The project is supervised by Docent Katariina Öörni (WRI; biochemistry,\r\n    cardiovascular disease) and Docent Matti Pirinen (FIMM; statistics,\r\n    computation).\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Salary and contract:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    A contract for up to 18 months is available starting as soon as possible.\r\n    The salary is based on the salary of University of Helsinki and depends on\r\n    the qualification and previous experience of the candidate. There will be a\r\n    trial period of 8 months. Applications are considered as they arrive until\r\n    the position is filled.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Applications are submitted by sending (1) motivation letter and CV in a\r\n    single PDF file and (2) transcript of academic records by e-mail to\r\n    kati.oorni(at)\r\n    \u003ca href="http://wri.fi/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"\u003e\r\n        wri.fi\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    For further information, please contact Katariina Öörni at the above e-mail\r\n    address.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
