    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eUsability Specialist, Team Coordinator\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We are now seeking a Usability Specialist to join our User Experience team for one year as a maternity leave substitute in our Clinical Diagnostics\r\n    Division R\u0026amp;D organization in Vantaa, Finland. The person would be working in two major In Vitro Diagnostic (IVD) medical device projects and would also\r\n    coordinate the work of our User Experience team.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Responsibilities:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Performing and documenting the usability validation of an IVD medical device in accordance with the regulatory requirements (travelling both in Europe and\r\n    in the USA required).\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Participating in a major IVD product development project, performing and documenting usability assessments, managing use-related requirements and risks and\r\n    supporting the project team in questions related to usability and ergonomics.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Coordinating the daily work of a small User Experience team from July 2016 to February 2017, ensuring the correct timing of usability actions in all the\r\n    ongoing projects.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Required Experience and Qualifications:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e\r\n    Master´s or Bachelor´s degree in an applicable field\r\n\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e\r\n    Strong experience in usability testing and other user experience activities\r\n\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e\r\n    Excellent documentation skills\r\n\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e\r\n    Very good spoken and written Finnish and English\r\n\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We Additionally Value:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e\r\n    Experience in working with the usability of products with both hardware and software user interface\r\n\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e\r\n    Experience in working on a highly regulated field\r\n\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e\r\n    Knowledge of our Customers’ (hospitals, laboratories) work environment and of the European and FDA medical device regulations on usability and user\r\n    interface\r\n\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We are looking for a real team player who completes the assigned tasks efficiently and systematically in a timely manner. You enjoy working with wide\r\n    variety of people representing different roles and nationalities, and you also fluently handle the documentation work. We offer the possibility of working\r\n    in exciting global product development projects and coordinating the work of our UX team, which we are planning to increase in 2017.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We hope that you would be able to join our team in May at the latest.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Should you have any questions, please contact User Experience Manager Taina Tähtinen (tel. +358 10 329 2467). Application together with CV and salary\r\n    suggestions should be sent no later than 31th of March 2016 at\r\n    \u003ca href="https://internaljobs.thermofisher.com/job/vantaa/usability-specialist-team-coordinator/3362/1640675"\u003e\r\n        https://internaljobs.thermofisher.com/job/vantaa/usability-specialist-team-coordinator/3362/1640675\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    .\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
