    description:
      'We are looking for a Research Assistant to improve our existing web application for Drug Target Commons (DTC), \u003ca href="https://drugtargetcommons.fimm.fi"\u003ehttps://drugtargetcommons.fimm.fi\u003c/a\u003e, a crowd-sourcing platform aimed at improving the consensus on drug-target interactions. The existing database system and its web application allow users to search, submit, approve, filter, sort, or export/import data. The existing platform is developed using Visual Studio .NET and Postgres SQL. We want to improve the user interface design, add more features to the web application and migrate the middleware to Python. Estimated duration of the work is 3-12 months, starting as soon as possible, but extension is also possible beyond this period. We welcome applications from experienced web-developers as well as masters students with web-application skills interested in a summer internship or thesis project.\r\n\r\nEssential skills:\r\n\r\nCSS, HTML, Java script, JQuery, Python, PostgreSQL.\r\n\r\nOptional skills:\r\n\r\nMongoDB, MySQL, ASP.NET, PHP, Perl.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested, please contact \u003ca href="mailto:gopal.peddinti@fimm.fi"\u003egopal.peddinti@fimm.fi\u003c/a\u003e with your CV and motivation letter. To read more about our research activities, please refer to \u003ca href="https://www.fimm.fi/en/research/groups/aittokallio"\u003ehttps://www.fimm.fi/en/research/groups/aittokallio\u003c/a\u003e',
