    description:
      '\u003ch3\u003eA little bit about us\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Digital Foodie is a software company specialized in the grocery business and the creator of award-winning Foodie.fm platform. We employ grocery industry\r\n    experts and technology specialists in four locations, and work closely with supermarket chains and local stores in several countries helping them to grow\r\n    their business. In addition to a world-class online grocery platform, we help our customers with product photography and data capture, business and\r\n    marketing planning, process optimization and store training.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat we do at Foodie Backend\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Our day-to-day work at the backend team consists of\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Developing and maintaining the APIs and data stores on top of which all our products are built\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Building and maintaining interfaces to external services and data sources according to customer requirements and\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Administering our clusters of Linux server instances in Amazon AWS environment\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Our core set of tools and technologies includes Ruby, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, AWS, Docker and Kubernetes.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003ch3\u003eWho are we looking for\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We are looking for someone with an ability and interest for developing practical, real world solutions and production ready code. You must be willing to\r\n    get your hands dirty and able to learn new tools and technologies with the help of the rest of our backend team. In addition, you must\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Have real-world software development experience with one or more modern programming languages\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Have experience with (relational) databases\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Have fluent English communication skills\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Understand the importance of good engineering practices: version control, documentation, tests, continuous integration\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We also value familiarity with any of the specific technologies we use, real world experience in web services development, and knowledge of cloud\r\n    infrastructure. You’ll get extra bonus points for being able to demonstrate personal pet projects or participation in open source software development.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat do we offer\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Fun and interesting work in an inspiring and steady-growing company that is enabling us to plan and buy our daily groceries\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        An opportunity to lead the expansion of world class grocery retail service together with industry experts in a forward-thinking and international\r\n        environment\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003ch3\u003ePracticalities\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You will be working at Foodie’s headquarters in Sörnäinen, Helsinki.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Please send your application including your CV and salary request to \u003ca href="mailto:anna.eronen@finitec.fi"\u003eanna.eronen@finitec.fi\u003c/a\u003e. Any github commits\r\n    or links to code you’ve written would be very much appreciated. The position will be filled as soon as possible.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nRegarding possible further information enquiries at this phase please write to Anna Eronen at    \u003ca href="mailto:anna.eronen@finitec.fi"\u003eanna.eronen@finitec.fi\u003c/a\u003e or call +358 40 522 3928.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    All applications are treated with confidentiality.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
