    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\nWould you like to join the Foreca Team in Keilaniemi? We are a group of programmers and scientists. We build accurate, beautiful and reliable weather products for global clients such as Microsoft, TomTom, BMW, and others.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nIf you love programming, we are interested in learning more about you. If you are already familiar with C++, PHP, SQL, Redis, Perl, or Web Map Services we consider it a bonus.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nPlease send your application and CV to \u003ca href="wanted@foreca.com"\u003ewanted@foreca\u003c/a\u003e.com now or by April 15th, 2016 at the latest. More information from Kimmo Kärkkäinen (Development Manager): \u003ca href="mailto:kimmo.karkkainen@foreca.com"\u003ekimmo.karkkainen@foreca.com\u003c/a\u003e, +358-50-4433295\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003ch3\u003eAbout Foreca\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nWe are a leading provider of digital weather data for business use worldwide. Our weather products are used daily by hundreds of millions of people. We have offices in Espoo, Stockholm and Moscow.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nForeca has a product and service portfolio ranging from ready-to-use graphical elements and applications to robust raw data interfaces and proven capability to provide digital weather services everywhere in the world.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
