    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Your summer will consist of project work either in one of our external\r\n    client projects or in an internal development project - or perhaps a bit of\r\n    both. You will be working alongside an experienced cross disciplinary team\r\n    to learn the secrets of modern software consulting. In previous years our\r\n    summer workers have worked in projects like OP face recognition payment and\r\n    backend of Iltasanomat evening magazine.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Don’t worry, we don’t expect you to know everything beforehand. You will be\r\n    mentored by a senior developer to maximize your learning and growth and to\r\n    ensure you get the most out of your Futurice experience. The main\r\n    expectation for you is to be willing and able to learn a lot. If you’re up\r\n    for it, there may be a possibility to continue Futurice career after the\r\n    summer.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Here’s a little checklist to help you figure out if we are a match for each\r\n    other\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        You have most of your relevant programming studies behind you and your\r\n        graduation may be lurking around the corner, or have otherwise got a\r\n        hold of things well enough because of your passion for digital things.\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        You have already done some cool code that actually works either on a\r\n        web browser, a mobile device, or in virtual world. We want to see what\r\n        you have created!\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        You really want to learn more about programming and one day become a\r\n        world-class professional in this.\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        You are fluent in English, and if you master also Finnish that’s a plus\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Gather your most awesome study/hobby projects, then add a transcript of\r\n    your studies. Spice these up with a short letter telling about who you are,\r\n    and how you are going to grow into a real software developer, and send\r\n    these to us. Don’t forget to mention your student organisation or guild\r\n    background - we like community oriented people. For more inspiration we\r\n    have created an article about\r\n    \u003ca href="http://futurice.com/blog/five-steps-to-a-great-application"\u003e\r\n        how to write great job applications\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    .\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Send your application by 2nd of December at latest.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The Company\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Futurice is built on a strong foundation of people, culture and\r\n    collaboration. We use our strengths to help our clients change, innovate\r\n    and build fantastic digital services. We are over 500 passionate\r\n    developers, designers and strategists working out of 7 offices in 5\r\n    countries. Our ways of working are all about speed and agility, and our\r\n    culture about transparency, caring, trust and continuous improvement.\r\nYou’ll get the full experience starting from our    \u003ca href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Lu36i1UQgk8"\u003eOnboarding camp™\u003c/a\u003e\r\nand of course you get to join our    \u003ca href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u0Ds6t2M2Qk"\u003eFutucamp\u003c/a\u003e with all\r\n    the futuriceans across Europe.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Got questions?\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Santtu Seppänen\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    +358 40 8313429\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
