    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We are looking for a back-end developer with Python/Django skills.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Do you want your work to be meaningful? Do you want your workplace to feel right for you? Do you want to create something new and be a part of the digital\r\n    revolution in healthcare?\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We are now recruiting our first employees to Helsinki, Finland. If you want ownership in what you do and your mindset is innovative, creative and\r\n    international; we are looking for you.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You would be developing leading-edge patient-centric mobile solutions for children’s hospitals that bring together families and healthcare providers,\r\n    ensuring children’s well-being and happiness. As you will be one of the first joiners in our new company, you will naturally be involved in building our\r\n    organization culture and ways of working.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003ch2\u003e\r\n    Job description\r\n\u003c/h2\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You would be responsible of programming the RESTful API that the mobile apps use and programming the web user interface to administer the system and\r\n    designing and maintaining the data model.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    In future you would be doing integrations to different the healthcare systems like Epic, Cerner, ESKO and Uranus.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Part of the work would be to maintain a good documentation of the REST API.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    In order to succeed you would need:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Python \u0026amp; Django skills\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Skills designing REST API with good security practices\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        SQL / PostgreSQL skills\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        HTML \u0026amp; CSS skills\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Javascript skills\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Familiar with good version control (Git) practises\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    It’s a plus if you have knowledge of:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Different healthcare related security standards and regulations e.g. HIPAA\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Cloud hosting platforms e.g. Azure, AWS, Google Cloud Platform\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003ch2\u003e\r\n    About Buddy Healthcare\r\n\u003c/h2\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We are a Finnish start-up company with a vision of offering the best patient-centric mobile solutions for children’s hospitals. We are currently developing\r\n    our solution together with major children’s hospitals in the US and Finland. Our first pilot project is expected to launch shortly.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Our vision is to grow into an ecosystem that is present in families’ lives throughout childhood bringing together children, families, healthcare providers\r\n    and other partners ensuring children’s well-being and happiness. Our youthful team is located in Helsinki. Reaching our global growth targets require a lot\r\n    of work, but we want to enjoy what we do and maintain a laid-back work environment.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003ch2\u003e\r\n    More information\r\n\u003c/h2\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nSend your application with CV and cover letter with links to possible hobby/open source projects by e-mail to    \u003ca href="mailto:jobs@buddyhealthcare.com"\u003ejobs@buddyhealthcare.com\u003c/a\u003e . To get more information, call our CTO Jukka Hassinen +358 40 736 4090.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
