    description:
      '\u003cem\u003e\r\n    Frogmind is a Helsinki based game studio of 21 people, founded in 2012 and\r\n    operating in a long-term partnership with Supercell. Frogmind’s games have\r\n    won several awards such as the Apple Design Award, Apple iPad Game of the\r\n    Year, and IMGA Grand Prix, and they have been downloaded over 100 million\r\n    times. The latest Frogmind games are multiplayer PvP games Badland Brawl\r\n    and Rumble Stars Football. Our goal is simple: to develop and self-publish\r\n    games that stand out with the best possible gaming experience and high\r\n    production values by small independent teams of talented game developers\r\n    without managers. As we believe in flat hierarchy and small independent\r\n    teams, we are looking for proactive developers who want to contribute to\r\n    our games in every way possible to make them the best in the world. Because\r\n    of this spirit, everyone at Frogmind owns part of the company through our\r\n    option plan. Check out the trailers for Rumble Stars Football here and\r\n    Badland Brawl here!\r\n\u003c/em\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Frogmind is now looking for a new Backend Developer to design and create\r\n    their mobile games’ scalable backend tech. As Backend Developer, you play a\r\n    big role in game server architecture planning, implementation, deployment,\r\n    and maintenance (be it logic, network, or database design, to mention a few\r\n    examples). You get to code real-time live systems and leave your mark in\r\n    the coolest of games. Frogmind currently has four live games and there are\r\n    more in the making. At Frogmind, everyone loves games and everything\r\n    related to them. That is why every single feature, graphics asset, and\r\n    sound in their games is carefully designed and handcrafted. They believe\r\n    that small, independent teams with talented, passionate people create the\r\n    best games – Frogmind does not believe in managers. Everyone at Frogmind is\r\n    a game developer, and currently there are 21 of them in the company.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cstrong\u003eRequirements for the applicant:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Previous scalable backend development work experience (from one\r\n        previous position, at least)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Strong skills in the following tech stack: Java, AWS, database design\r\n        and implementation (SQL), Linux shell\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Understanding of what it means to support large user volumes\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Working proficiency in English, both oral and written\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eFrogmind offers you:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cul\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Freedom to design your own workflow\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Freedom to choose your own laptop/workstation\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Competitive compensation including an option plan (everyone in\r\n            Frogmind is an owner of the company)\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Opportunity to work with skilled industry veterans in a team of 21\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Possibility to work in a well connected studio known for excellence\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Being part of making the best games and impact the gaming industry\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Flexibility considering working hours and times\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            \u003cstrong\u003eSkill tags: \u003c/strong\u003e\r\n            Java, AWS, database design and implementation (SQL), Linux shell\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            \u003cstrong\u003eRead more and apply by the 19th of August\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n            :\r\n            \u003ca\r\n                href="https://atalent.fi/en/open-position/backend-developer-8?utm_source=tkoaly\u0026amp;utm_medium=email"\r\n                target="_blank"\r\n            \u003e\r\n                https://atalent.fi/en/\r\n                \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n                    open-position/backend-\r\n                    \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n                        developer-8?utm_source=tkoaly\u0026amp;\r\n                        \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n                            utm_medium=email\r\n                        \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n                    \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n                \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n            \u003c/a\u003e\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n',
