    description:
      "\u003cp\u003eYep, that's the feeling. Digging into the source of an awesome web page to find clues on how a certain thing is made. Maybe you want to see which JavaScript libraries were used, or if that effect was done with pure CSS. Or maybe you'd rather take a look of the markup structure and code to figure out which frameworks and APIs lie under the bonnet.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eWhether it's JavaScript, Scala, Clojure, Java, or .NET, web is your thing. It's not just about getting the data to flow from the database to the user's screen. It's about getting to know the technologies, understanding the layers and finally offering a great user experience. A browser is not just a rendering tool, it's your medium of choice.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eFuturice is always looking for talented web developers to work with backend and frontend technologies. We offer an international work environment where you get to work with and learn from some of the best developers and designers in the field. \u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eRead more and send your application at http://futurice.com/open-positions/full-stack-developer-helsinki, or send us an open application to careers.helsinki@futurice.com.\u003c/p\u003e",
