    description:
      '\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Helsinki University Library is the largest multidisciplinary university library in Finland. The Library is the employer of 170 librarians and other\r\n        library professionals and its operational expenses are about 21 million euros. Helsinki University Library is an independent institute of the\r\n        University of Helsinki. The Library operates on all of the four university campuses as well as online.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        ATTX 2016 is a new a new research and development project run by the Helsinki University Library as part of the national Open Science and Research\r\n        initiative. The goal of the project is to put research related data to good use. The project will be developing software components for linking,\r\n        enriching and distributing linked data and provide solution for turning published datasets into scalable and robust data services.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Three person project group will include project manager and two responsible specialists. Work will be driven by concrete use cases, so the project\r\n        group will be knee-deep in data from the beginning to the end. Use cases will be implemented together with the universities and other parties involved\r\n        in different stages of the research process. Project will rely heavily on open source software and all the contributions of the project will be made\r\n        openly available.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Helsinki university library invites applications for the position of\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        LINKED OPEN DATA SPECIALIST\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        for a fixed term position from 1.9.2016 to 31.12.2017. There is a four month trial period for the position.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        The person will be in charge of designing and implementing the data layer for the ATTX 2016 project. Tasks included development of internal data\r\n        processing components and RDF based data storage as well as the design of the internal data model. Selected candidate is also expected to participate\r\n        in other project related software development activities, which are led by the other members of the project group.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        In addition to general software development experience, the successful candidate understands and has experience in graph based data processing.\r\n        Applicant should also know the meaning of the following acronyms: RDF, SPARQL, SHACL, PROV, HDT and LDF.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Familiarity with semantic web technologies and experience in implementing and using ontology and rule based systems is considered as an advantage.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Because we are a small project group, selected candidate is excepted to be able to show initiative and courage in the face of the unknown and to take\r\n        responsibility for the assigned tasks and work packages. Position requires good knowledge of Finnish and English.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        The salary will be based on level 9 of the job requirement scheme for non-research personnel in the salary system of Finnish universities. In addition,\r\n        the appointee will receive a salary component based on personal work performance. The total monthly salary will be determined depending on the\r\n        appointee\'s qualifications and experience.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Please submit your application using the University of Helsinki Recruitment System via the link Apply for job. Applicants who are current employees of\r\n        the University of Helsinki are requested to leave their application via the SAP HR portal. The closing date for applications is August 21, 2016.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Further information about the position may be obtained from project manager Joonas Kesäniemi, Tel. +358 504151688, joonas.kesaniemi(at)helsinki.fi.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Apply at latest 21.08.2016\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003ch4\u003e\r\n        AP­PLY LINK\r\n    \u003c/h4\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        \u003ca\r\n            href="https://rekry.helsinki.fi/sap/bc/erecruiting/posting_apply?param=cG9zdF9pbnN0X2d1aWQ9MTA2MDRCOTkyN0M4MUVFNjk2QUJDRTJGMjREOURENjcmY2FuZF90eXBlPQ%3D%3D\u0026amp;sap-client=300\u0026amp;BspClient=300\u0026amp;BspLanguage=EN\u0026amp;sap-language=EN"\r\n        \u003e\r\n            https://rekry.helsinki.fi/sap/bc/erecruiting/posting_apply?param=cG9zdF9pbnN0X2d...\r\n        \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003ch4\u003e\r\n        DUE DATE\r\n    \u003c/h4\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Sunday, August 21, 2016\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e',
