    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWe are looking for a senior backend developer to join our 20 specialists in the Yle Areena team.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eYou will develop Yle Areena, that has been nominated several times as the most valued web brand in Finland. Yle Areena has millions of users, so your work will have a direct impact on everyday life of Finns.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eWe work in a truly agile and self-organized team. Development work is done primarily with Clojure, with a splash of Scala as well. We hope that you have also some experience with open source development, functional programming languages, AWS environment and JavaScript. We are deploying code to production daily. Fluent Finnish language skill is a mandatory requirement.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eWork is done at Yle premises in Pasila together with collegues that come from other top IT companies. Organizational boundaries are practically irrelevant when we make Yle Areena. We solve the most difficult problems together, but otherwise we offer you possibility to focus on your code without interruptions.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eSend us your application as soon as possible here \u003ca href="http://affecto.catsone.com/careers/index.php?m=portal\u0026a=apply\u0026jobOrderID=6997116\u0026portalID=52323" target="_blank"\u003ehttp://affecto.catsone.com/careers/index.php?m=portal\u0026a=apply\u0026jobOrderID=6997116\u0026portalID=52323\u003c/a\u003e \u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMORE INFORMATION\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMarko Loukkola\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\r\ntel. +358 44 552 5952\u003cbr\u003e\r\nfirstname.lastname[at]affecto.com\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ci\u003eAffecto is a leading information and analytics company in Northern Europe that employs over 1000 experts in nine different countries. We solve our customer’s business challenges by combining analytics, service design and agile software development. Teams from Affecto have won in 2005 for example Slush Ultrahack and Nordic IoT -hackathons.\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n',
    begin: "2016-07-04",
    end: "2017-01-01",
