    tags: [],
    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n\u003ci\u003eAre you a software developer with a passion for end-user experience?\u003c/i\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We’re looking for recent graduates for Junior Software Designer position, or you should be at least at the end of your studies. From University as well as\r\n    from University of applied sciences – It’s the attitude that counts. We’re on a hunt for fresh talent that’s equipped with hands-on, energetic and adaptive\r\n    attitude.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You will be helping our software development team solve customer business needs by designing and building modern and efficient custom software solutions.\r\n    Building the next generation of user experience driven digital services in challenging customer projects, you will participate in Affecto’s end-to-end\r\n    solution delivery.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eWhat we expect:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n    – Basic Linux experience (scripting)\r\n\r\n    – Device configuration\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    – Programming languages on basic level: Python, C++\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    – Cloud service experience (Installa a server, for instance, on AWS)\r\n\r\n    – Algorithm Design\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003ePlusses:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    – Machine vision, data analytics (Maybe courses in university)\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    – Java\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    – Javascript\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    For you to be successful in the role, you need to be able to step into the shoes of the end-user to help him/her in their everyday life. Previous\r\n    experience in software projects (work or a hobby) and knowledge of Linux (Ubuntu, Debian or RedHat) will be seen as a benefit. Here at Affecto you will\r\n    have a splendid opportunity to learn a lot about video analytics in cloud-based service and IoT projects. Your location will be Helsinki.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    At Affecto we embrace the individual in each of us, with the firm convincing that people do their best work when they can feel free to be who they are. We\r\n    strive to nurture independence, mutual respect, responsibility and accountability in everything we do. You will work with Northern Europe’s top talent\r\n    within the field.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    If that sounds like something that would ignite your spark, then do get in touch with us and send your CV. We will keep the position open until we find a\r\n    suitable candidate, so we urge you to submit your application sooner rather than later.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nWould you like more information about the job itself? Vesa Kuoppala is glad to give further details – feel free to contact him:    \u003ca href="mailto:vesa.kuoppala@affecto.com"\u003evesa.kuoppala@affecto.com\u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eApply:\u003c/strong\u003e \u003ca href="http://affecto.com/open-positions/junior-software-developer" target="_blank"\u003ehttp://affecto.com/open-positions/junior-software-developer/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n',
