    description:
      "\u003cp\u003eOur AR/VR/MR dev department is growing and we are looking for a Intern Developer to join our team. \r\nSoftability Group is a Microsoft Partner and your main environment will be Windows for Hololens device. \r\nWe also have plans for AR/VR so knowing about iOS and Android as well as general mobile development is a bonus.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eSkills \u0026 Requirements\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eYou are currently studying for a Bsc or Master in Computer Science or Software engineering related studies.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eYou are at least in your third year of study and have completed a minimum of 150ects. \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eYou already completed your first internship.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eYou are an ambitious developer with some basic experience in software development with .NET/C# and Unity technologies.\u003c/li\u003e \r\n\u003cli\u003eYou have been using Unity for personal and school projects.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eYou have attended classes on C# and/or Unity.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eYou are interested in the newest technologies.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eYou communicate fluently in both Finnish and English language.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eRequired skills:\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e Proven track in C# (knowledge of OOP basics, inheritance, event pattern, encapsulation and so on)\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e 1 year of Unity usage\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e Version control with git (commit, push, pull, log)\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e You understand AR/VR/MR techonologies\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003e You have a portfolio and a linkedin account\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nThe internship is paid and the suitable candidate may be offered a permanent position at the end of the internship.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nIf you found yourself interested and fit the requirements then please send your cover letter, a link to your LinkedIn profile and your portfolio to rekrytointi@softability.fi (all three are mandatory). \r\n\u003cbr /\u003eLooking forward hearing from you!\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eRead more about us and our employees at http://www.softability.fi/ura.\r\n\u003cbr /\u003e\r\nFor further information please contact CEO Janne Repo janne.repo@softability.fi or +358 40 550 8280.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nAbout Softability Group Oy\r\n\u003cbr /\u003e\r\nSoftability is an innovative, profitable and growing software house located at Vantaa, Finland with 40+ consultants. We have a flat and agile organizational structure combined with a high trust and international work environment. We were born as a spin-off from ThermoFisher Scientific, a medical device manufacturer, in 2002 which influences a lot the way we do business today and with whom we do it with.\u003c/p\u003e",
