    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Tuxera overview\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Tuxera is one of the fastest growing software companies in Finland. We are a global organization and the market leader in data storage solutions and\r\n    interoperability software. With a growing team of over 60 professionals from more than 17 nationalities, we have been recognized with awards such as Great\r\n    Place to Work. Our software ships inside 10 billion devices on the market, including smartphones, routers, laptops, cars, TVs, drones and many others.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Our mission: to open the way for people and businesses to reliably store, access, and share any type of data on any device. We envision a future with an\r\n    infinite number of connected devices. With Tuxera at the heart of every device, data is always accessible exactly when and where you want it to be.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Job description\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    As a DevOps Lead Engineer - Embedded Solutions you will ensure that our software of pristine quality is produced and delivered quickly. You will build\r\n    ruthless automation and streamline R\u0026amp;D operations to the delight of our customers and engineers. Your guiding principle is to enable the entire team to\r\n    effortlessly build, test and deploy their magic. In doing so you will nurture a product development effort that powers millions of consumer electronics\r\n    devices in the world.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Tasks and responsibilities\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Serving as a technical lead in design and implementation of DevOps systems and practices\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Pioneer continuous integration, testing and delivery activities and thus shorten the release cycle\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Collaborate with highly skilled development, QA and delivery engineers who build file system and other software solutions for embedded devices\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Background and qualifications\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Experienced professional who has worked in technical lead roles\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Proven experience in ramping up and maintaining continuous integration, test automation and delivery systems. E.g. Jenkins, Bamboo, Robot Framework,\r\n        xUnit, etc.\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        High proficiency in administrating Linux server environments\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Sound knowledge of virtualization technologies such as VMware vSphere, OpenStack, vagrant, Docker etc.\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Excellent programming skills especially scripting languages such as bash, Python, etc.\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        A genuine passion for enabling cutting-edge software development practices\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Knowledge of file systems and popular operating systems seen as a plus\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Tuxera offers you\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Dynamic and international work environment, with flexible working hours\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Dream setup: laptop + smartphone of your choice\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Personal health insurance\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Lunch coupons\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Hobby coupons (e.g., for gym, movies, theater, opera, etc)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    In addition to all these perks, we offer you a flexible work environment in which you’ll have the opportunity to work and drive your ideas forward using\r\n    the best ways and tools for you to get things done. We’ve been named Great Place to Work for a second year in a row because we enjoy being challenged and\r\n    value continuous learning and improvement. You’ll be working with some of the most resourceful, brilliant people in the software industry; in products and\r\n    projects for top global brands. We are also very active in tech communities, organizing, sponsoring and attending software meetups, hackathons, and other\r\n    industry events. We support your initiatives by offering you an opportunity to spend 10% of your working hours on related side projects, and offer you\r\n    great possibilities for personal and professional growth. We also offer you the rare opportunity to change the world such that everyone around you is using\r\n    the product you built. We’re not just another software company, we’re powering all the devices that are used by real people every day.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    How to apply\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The position will be filled once a suitable candidate is found. To apply, please send us your cover letter, CV and anything else that shows your skills via\r\n    the \u003ca href="http://www.tuxera.com/company/careers/job-application/?aguid=01790FC4CC1B4E17A82B9624356A1770"\u003elink\u003c/a\u003e. We look forward to receiving your application!\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
