    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eTrademarkNow\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    , winner of the 2015 and 2016 Gold Stevie® Award for Company of the Year – Legal, provides the only comprehensive trademark clearance solution that\r\n    delivers a clear picture of risk in seconds. With its unique likelihood-of-confusion algorithm, driven by 15 years of research, our web-based platform\r\n    helps in-house legal teams, law firms and branding agencies strengthen their trademark clearance process while saving them time and money. Created by\r\n    experts in trademark law and linguistics, our cutting-edge system also utilizes state-of-the-art machine-learning techniques to produce models that\r\n    seamlessly take real-world complexities into account. While the underlying intelligence is complex, the platform’s intuitive design and simple user\r\n    interface make it very easy to use. The result: faster, smarter trademark search, watch and analysis. \u003cstrong\u003ewww.trademarknow.com\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We are now looking for a part-time \u003cstrong\u003eSystem Administration Intern\u003c/strong\u003e to strengthen our brilliant Helsinki-based R\u0026amp;D team. Duration of the\r\n    internship will be 4 to 6 months and working hours are between 20 to 37,5 h per week. In this position you will be reporting to our CTO Matti Kokkola. In\r\n    addition to the system admin work you will be given other supportive tasks as well depending on your background and interests.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    If you are looking for a part-time job to support your studies, this could be the perfect opportunity for you!\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eWhat do I need to have?\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Comfortable working with and configuring Ubuntu Linux servers\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Great troubleshooting skills\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Linux scripting skills\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Willingness to automate routine tasks instead of doing them manually\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Ability to work effectively in a collaborative environment\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Studies from a relevant field (e.g. Computer Science or equivalent technical discipline)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Interest and proactive efforts in advancing one’s technical skill sets is required\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Ability to document what you have done\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Strong communication skills in English (Finnish is a plus!)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Technical buzz words related to the task: Ansible, Bash, Ubuntu, Jenkins etc\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eWhat do I need to be great at?\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Rolling up your sleeves; you will need to be flexible and adaptable in your approach; must be able to work as part of a multi-disciplinary team,\r\n        providing support to other areas of the business if and when required\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Self-Starter, results orientated with a positive outlook and a clear focus on high quality.\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        High levels of integrity, and organizational and cultural awareness combined with sound communication skills\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Strong team player and collaborative approach – happy to ‘get stuck in’ as needed\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        And finally, you will want an opportunity to grow in an exciting new global startup and will enjoy the requisite benefits that such an employer could\r\n        offer, namely international travel, being part of a company where you will get to help set and shape the company culture in a big way and fantastic\r\n        growth opportunities.\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eCore Values of TrademarkNow\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Autonomy: TrademarkNow is a flat organization; everyone has a say; employees are trusted\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Mastery: TrademarkNow\'s employees hunger for new challenges; are professionally curious; are constantly learning new professional abilities and skills\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Work-life balance: TrademarkNow supports its employees in striking their preferred balance between "work" (career and ambition) and "lifestyle"\r\n        (health, pleasure, leisure, family, etc.)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Culture of experimentation, but also of accountability: TrademarkNow allows its people to experiment (and to fail so that they can learn), but also\r\n        holds them accountable where appropriate\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Solutions, not problems attitude: TrademarkNow\'s people tend to take the initiative to solve problems and bring solutions to the company, rather than\r\n        just raising them as complaints\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Customer centricity / think like the customer: TrademarkNow\'s people ensure that our customers and their needs are at the center of everything we do\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Globality / taking over the world: TrademarkNow\'s people are worldly and focused on big goals\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nIf you got interested, please send your CV, latest course transcript and cover letter to our Talent \u0026amp; People Manager Katariina Hava (    \u003ca href="mailto:katariina.hava@trademarknow.com)"\u003ekatariina.hava@trademarknow.com)\u003c/a\u003e. Please, also let us know what is the best timing for you to do the\r\n    internship. \u003cstrong\u003eApplication period ends 30\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003csup\u003eth\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e of November\u003c/strong\u003e and after this the most potential\r\n    candidates will be invited to the interview round. Feel free to contact Katariina with any questions related to the recruitment process!\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
