    tags: [],
    description:
      '\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        ‘WHAT WOULD I BE DOING’, YOU ASK?\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Some of our most recent work includes building cloud backends and\r\n        architectures for financial institutions, healthcare sector, retail and\r\n        logistics. Machine learning, data analysis and data pipelines are also\r\n        things our developers work on regularly. The daily work of our backend\r\n        developers consists of designing and building infrastructures,\r\n        microservices and scalable backends. So real, heavy, hands-on\r\n        programming. That’s what we do. Being consultants and experts in our\r\n        field, we also consult our customers on the best technologies and\r\n        solutions, usually already in the sales phase of the project. But the\r\n        main part of the work is being a developer, working closely with the\r\n        customer.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Your previous GCP experience ensures that you will be easily absorbed\r\n        into our projects. If you’re new to GCP, not to worry! You’ll get a\r\n        chance to learn more and get certified. And there are a lot of\r\n        colleagues to help you along the way. In addition to coding, you will\r\n        be mentoring your juniors, as well as arranging and attending tech\r\n        events. And if you feel like sharing your knowledge in our meetups,\r\n        you’re more than welcome to host and present.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        We’ll provide you with tools and opportunities to develop your skills\r\n        further, as well as the freedom to come up with your own ways to create\r\n        infra. You will also have the opportunity to create your own\r\n        development path as a professional. Our coaching process supports you\r\n        if you want to be a backend-developer-turned-into-a-cloud-architect,\r\n        or, e.g. get more heavily into data science. No matter what your\r\n        position in our backend team would be when you arrive at Qvik, you can\r\n        be sure that there are a lot of development possibilities available.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        WHO ARE YOU?\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        You’re either a senior level backend master, or well on your way there.\r\n        You know your way around the essentials such as Node.js, Python and its\r\n        frameworks, and Go. You probably have previous experience in GCP or AWS\r\n        cloud solutions, even certifications, or at least have the hunger to\r\n        learn. You may already be familiar with managed platforms. You enjoy\r\n        building and designing infrastructures, and are on fire when talking\r\n        about anything running on the App Engine.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        If you already are an architect or aim at becoming one, you probably\r\n        have a deep understanding of, among others, network design, serverless\r\n        design patterns, container orchestration (Kubernetes, Docker), cloud\r\n        native architecture designs and managed services. Your programming\r\n        skills are on a senior level, and you want to keep your hands on the\r\n        keyboard in the future, as well. For you, orchestrating containers\r\n        instead of servers is the best thing and microservices the way to go.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        You want to work in a team, be a good colleague and deeply understand\r\n        the needs of a customer. You know agile methodologies and have good\r\n        Finnish language skills.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        If you want to hear more about this opportunity, call to our Head of\r\n        Cloud and hiring manager Jari Lindholm, tel. +358 40 530 1626. We only\r\n        accept applications sent via our recruitment system.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        INTERESTED?\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Our office is located in the heart of Helsinki in Kamppi shopping\r\n        center office spaces.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        We offer our low hierarchy culture; opportunities to try, fail and\r\n        succeed; as well as a chance for you to concentrate on your actual\r\n        work. That’s what you would come here for, right?\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Our benefits package is also pretty nice with flexible working hours,\r\n        the work equipment of your choice; lunch coupons; commuter, culture and\r\n        sports benefits; occupational health care with extra insurance;\r\n        company-paid massage; and many sports and hobby possibilities with\r\n        other Qvikies.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        In addition to many work-related guilds and other development\r\n        opportunities, we arrange a lot of internal and external get-togethers\r\n        and events throughout the year, in Finland and abroad.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Send us your application - We’ll fill the positions as soon as we find\r\n        the right match!\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003ca\r\n    href="https://emp.jobylon.com/applications/jobs/18062/create/"\r\n    target="_blank"\r\n\u003eAPPLY\r\n\u003c/a\u003e',
