    description:
      '\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        2017 is the year when you can quit the navy and become a pirate.\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cbr /\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        Emblica is a company owned by two HYCS students. Currently we’re\r\n        working with clients and partners such as Slush, Otavamedia,\r\n        IndustryHack and UpCloud. Our focus is on Proof-of-Concepts, DevOps /\r\n        infra, web and analytics with the newest technologies.\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cbr /\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        In addition to client work, we’re working on a DevOps related SaaS\r\n        product and we’re also very interested in machine learning. We use and\r\nbelieve in open source and have some projects brewing at        \u003ca href="http://github.com/emblica"\u003egithub.com/emblica\u003c/a\u003e.\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n        Join us and let’s build a company together! The skills we are looking\r\n        for - that you have or are willing to learn:\r\n        \r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003cul\u003e\r\n        \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                Solid programming skills\r\n            \u003c/div\u003e\r\n        \r\n            \u003cul\u003e\r\n                \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n                    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                        Python, JS/Node, Clojure (or Ruby, Go, Rust, any\r\n                        functional languages)\r\n                    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n                \u003c/li\u003e\r\n                \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n                    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                        bonus: C, C++, Java, C#\r\n                    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n                \u003c/li\u003e\r\n            \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                DevOps\r\n            \u003c/div\u003e\r\n            \u003cul\u003e\r\n                \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n                    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                        Linux, Docker, Ansible, cloud (AWS, UpCloud)\r\n                    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n                \u003c/li\u003e\r\n                \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n                    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                        bonus: Chef, Puppet, CircleCI, TravisCI, Heroku,\r\n                        Jenkins\r\n                    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n                \u003c/li\u003e\r\n            \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                Common server software\r\n            \u003c/div\u003e\r\n            \u003cul\u003e\r\n                \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n                    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                        Nginx, MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, ElasticSearch\r\n                    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n                \u003c/li\u003e\r\n                \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n                    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                        bonus: Apache, HAproxy, Kafka, bash scripting\r\n                    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n                \u003c/li\u003e\r\n            \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                Data analytics / machine learning experience\r\n            \u003c/div\u003e\r\n            \u003cul\u003e\r\n                \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n                    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                        bonus: Python based tools, Spark, Tensorflow\r\n                    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n                \u003c/li\u003e\r\n            \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    We can offer different positions based on your skills and ambitions:\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            Freelancer / student friendly (we can also take contractors)\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            Part-time / full-time\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            Junior / senior partner\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    Perks:\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            Work anytime, anywhere, as much as you want - absolutely no\r\n            corporate bs\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            Want gym / lunch vouchers? Let’s talk.\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            Stick with us =\u0026gt; money, fame and glory (pick your poison)\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \r\n        \u003cul\u003e\r\n            \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n                \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                    stock options, equity (ownership of company) for employees\r\n                    and partners\r\n                \u003c/div\u003e\r\n            \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            Let’s figure out something crazy: work abroad for a month? Company\r\n            trip to a 5-star resort? Beat the owners in game/sport of your\r\n            choosing? We’re open for all of this.\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\nGet in touch with us at    \u003ca href="mailto:hello@emblica.fi"\u003ehello@emblica.fi\u003c/a\u003e or try ping elnygren\r\n    / theikkila at IRCnet. We don’t need a formal CV or job application -\r\n    introduce yourself and let’s go for a beer / coffee / lunch (Yay! we’ll\r\n    pay!).\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    - Elias Nygrén \u0026amp;\u0026amp; Teemu Heikkilä\r\n\u003c/div\u003e',
