    description:
      '\u003cheader\u003e\r\n    \u003ch1\u003e\r\n        QlikView Specialist\r\n    \u003c/h1\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        Category: Business Analysis (functional and technical)\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        City: Helsinki, Uusimaa, Finland\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        Position ID: J1118-0935\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        Employment Type: Full Time\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003c/header\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        \u003ch2\u003e\r\n            Position Description:\r\n        \u003c/h2\u003e\r\n        \u003cp id="jd"\u003e\r\n            We are looking for a QlikView Specialist to join our team for a\r\n            client assignment. We have an agile team of 6 members working\r\n            closely together with the client. Our team is working on two\r\n            fronts; on areas of ETL (Informatica) and reporting (Qlikview \u0026amp;\r\n            SSRS).\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            The main responsibility of the role is to develop Qlikview\r\n            solutions for our client needs. The duties of the developer are\r\n            requirement analysis, technical design, implementation of a\r\n            solutions and post development activities such as test support and\r\n            deployment planning.\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            We offer:\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            We know that one of the key components of our success is the\r\n            talent, skills and knowledge of the people who join our team –\r\n            professionals like you. This is what we offer:\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            • Meaningful job and exciting tasks: You will work in challenging\r\n            projects with products and services that add true value to our\r\n            customers.\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            • Experienced and enthusiastic colleagues: You will be part of a\r\n            dynamic and innovative team where everyone’s knowledge and\r\n            competences are valued. We strive to create an environment where\r\n            our professionals enjoy working together and feel empowered.\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            • Excellent opportunities to learn and to develop yourself: Your\r\n            career and professional development will be our top priorities. We\r\n            offer many career paths, and various learning and development\r\n            programs.\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            • Benefits of a large and global IT company: We are one of the\r\n            leading IT companies in the world. In Finland we work locally and\r\n            customer-oriented. We combine strong local expertise, global\r\n            resources and certified business models.\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            We expect you to have:\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            • Ability and experience to develop Qlikview solutions\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            • Good communication skills in English\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            Additionally the role benefits from:\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            • Knowledge and experience of using Microsoft BI stack (SSRS, SSIS)\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            • Good communication skills in Finnish\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            Interested?\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            For more information, please contact Jukka Rantanen, Director\r\n            Consulting Services, 040 512 5620.\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            Apply now by clicking "I\'m interested".\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            Please leave your application by 01.01.2019 at the latest. We will\r\n            be screening and interviewing potential candidates during the\r\n            application period.\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            Personal security clearances will be required depending on the\r\n            role.\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003ca href="https://cgi.njoyn.com/cgi/xweb/Xweb.asp?tbtoken=ZVlfSh9fDVB3EHB0QVZTYE8%2FAW1eaVVZelJMIlkKDnlRXUZvKDYdBmAEB00YGhdTSXBlF3U%3D\u0026chk=dFlbQBJR\u0026clid=21001\u0026page=jobdetails\u0026jobid=J1118-0935\u0026BRID=EX653808\u0026SBDID=1\u0026LANG=1"\u003eAdditional information\u003c/a\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003c/div\u003e',
