    description:
      '\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    The HyperSnap project is looking for an Android developer to be part of our\r\n    core team. The developer will get a chance to create a proof-of-concept\r\n    application that enables use of the researched AI-based hyperspectral\r\n    imaging technology. The application will be made from scratch while working\r\n    closely with the rest of the team. The Android application is expected to\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    * Take images with custom settings (exposure, etc) using the mobile camera\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    * Send the images to the cloud for running algorithms\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    * Visualize spectral data allowing the user to explore shots\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    For more information see\r\n    \u003ca href="https://chra.gitlab.io/hypersnap/" target="_blank"\u003e\r\n        https://chra.gitlab.io/\r\n        \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n            hypersnap/\r\n        \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    The developer will be employed as a research assistant by the University of\r\n    Helsinki, and should preferrably have some experience with mobile\r\n    development. No previous experience in AI or hyperspectral imaging is\r\n    required, though an interest in photography is a bonus! The position is\r\n    either part-time or full-time, depending on the candidate\'s preferences.\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    If you are interested, let us know by contacting Chang Rajani (\r\n    \u003ca href="mailto:chra@cs.helsinki.fi" target="_blank"\u003e\r\n        chra@cs.helsinki.fi\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    ) by email, along with your CV and a transcript of study records. The\r\n    candidate is expected to start in September, but postponing the timing can\r\n    be arranged.\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n',
