    description:
      "\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Our Research group at the Computer Science Department, University of\r\n    Helsinki, has an immediate opening for:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    - a Bachelor's-level or Master's-level student,\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - about 20 hours per week (time is flexible),\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - over the next 3-4 months, further continuation possible.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The student should be comfortable with:\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - CSS, Javascript,\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - mongoDB,\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - python programming.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The candidate does not need to be a top-level expert in these, but s/he\r\n    should be very comfortable working with these. For example, s/he should be\r\n    ideally able to show some prior experience -- either work or class\r\n    projects, or similar.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    An interest in\r\n\u003cbr /\u003e\r\n\u003cstrong\u003elanguage applications\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003cbr /\u003e\r\n    or in\r\n\u003cbr /\u003e\r\n\u003cstrong\u003emachine learning\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003cbr /\u003e\r\n    is definitely a plus, but it is not a requirement -- someone who simply\r\n    likes database \u0026amp; front-end work is also welcome.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The candidate should enjoy learning new things and working with other\r\n    people. Pay level is proportional to level of studies completed, according\r\n    to University pay scales.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Interested persons should contact Dr. Roman Yangarber at\r\n\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003ca href=\"mailto:firstname.lastname@cs.helsinki.fi\"\u003e\r\n    firstname.lastname@cs.helsinki.fi\r\n\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e",
