    description:
      '    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Need a summer job? Elisa is evaluating capabilities of AR / VR\r\n            technologies to build future interfaces. We are looking for one\r\n            Service Designer and one Developer as summer workers / trainees to\r\n            build a team for this task.\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            And what would be a better way to evaluate possibilities, than\r\n            creating something concrete:\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n        \u003cul type="disc"\u003e\r\n            \u003cli\u003e\r\n                There are plenty of sensors in office buildings nowadays.\r\n                \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n                For example here at Elisa, you can see the CO2 production on\r\n                per room basis, making it possible to evaluate the amount of\r\n                persons inside. This kind of data could be then displayed to\r\n                person wandering around the office wearing AR gadget.\r\n            \u003c/li\u003e\r\n            \u003cli\u003e\r\n                AR/VR can bring the product catalogs to another level. Browsing\r\n                through products, choosing one and viewing it in 3D. This can\r\n                be further extended to include real-time comm with expert or\r\n                salesperson.\r\n            \u003c/li\u003e\r\n            \u003cli\u003e\r\n                Your task is to innovate more with your team!\r\n            \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            The target gadgets are (either) MS Hololens and HTC Vive. The\r\n            engine to use is Unity 3D, C# being the scripting language.\r\n            \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n            If you are interested and you possess knowledge on how to build 3D\r\n            applications using Unity3D and C# and you know how to make use of\r\n            Rest APIs, please tell us more about yourself. Send us your CV,\r\n            portfolio and description what you would like to create and learn\r\n            during the summer.\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e',
