    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\nHI, WE’RE LOOKING FOR A CODER TO BOLSTER OUR RANKS!\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nInterested in web-development? Join the development and planning of\r\nkuka.io -platform!\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nKuka gives voice to experts and helps journalists to make more diverse and multi-voiced journalism. Our mission is to broaden the scope of expertise used in the media and bring knowledge to the general public. A journalist can search for relevant contacts on our broad and up-to-date database of experts. Experts, on the other hand, are provided with a platform for commenting on current issues being discussed in public.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nKuka started in a pub, when two journalists and a scholar started to think of solutions for this problem. The problem is that the diversity of the experts commenting in the media is really low. Even though there is a large reserve of expertise in Finland, the experts utilized are often the ones that already appear frequently in the media.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nCurrently, Kuka has journalists from e.g. the following media companies: Helsingin Sanomat, Yle, Kauppalehti and Taloussanomat. Experts come from a wide spectrum of universities, research institutes and corporations.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nWe have just launched a new version of the web-application, and we’re looking for a sixth member to our team. We have flexible work-hours and the pay-per-hour is negotiable.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nTechnical expectations:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eHTML5, CSS3 (SASS), Javascript\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eNode.js + Express + MongoDB\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eGulp, Grunt or any other build tool\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eGit\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nOther beneficial aspects:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eFormer experience with front-end frameworks (knockout, vue, angular etc.)\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eFormer experience with cloud based application platforms (heroku etc.)\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eFormer work experience in coding\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eInterest in developing web-based applications, and a wish to learn and experience with new technologies\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eWillingness to work in a young start-up environment\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eGeneral interest for media and communication\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eA true desire for societal problems and how to tackle them\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eThe ability to take responsibility\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nSounds interesting? Feel free to send your CV to our CEO Mari Vaara\r\n\u003ca href="mailto:mari@kukahaku.fi"\u003emari@kukahaku.fi\u003c/a\u003e and we’ll be in touch as soon as possible! For further information you can also contact our coder Janne Saastamoinen \u003ca href="mailto:janne@kukahaku.fi"\u003ejanne@kukahaku.fi\u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
