    description:
      "\u003cstrong\u003eLocation: Sliema, Malta\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003ch1\u003e\r\n    Why apply for the Web Developer position?\r\n\u003c/h1\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You’ll get a ringside seat to learning on how to do professional affiliate\r\n    marketing in a dynamic start-up work environment. Fast growing\r\n    iGaming-company offers you good career opportunities.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eWe also provide:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        6 hour working days\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Monthly salary €2200–€2700 depending on skills and experience\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Performance based bonus\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        24 annual vacation days\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Flexible working hours\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Employee benefit package\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003ch3\u003e\r\n\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003ch3\u003e\r\n    Job description\r\n\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    As a Web Developer at Good Game Ltd you’ll design and create user and SEO\r\n    friendly websites. You will also be responsible for developing various\r\n    tools for client use as well as updating existing websites together with\r\n    the IT-team of the company.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You have both the back- and front-end covered and have a good understanding\r\n    on how to build well performing websites. A part of your job will also be\r\n    helping other employees with basic level IT problems with both macOS and\r\n    Windows operating systems and hardware.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003ch3\u003e\r\n\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003ch3\u003e\r\n    Responsibilities\r\n\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Building website themes based on finished designs and integrating them\r\n        with publishing systems (Mainly WordPress)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Developing back- and front-end functionalities like custom WordPress\r\n        plugins and PHP classes\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Helping other employees with basic IT-related problems\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003ch3\u003e\r\n\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003ch3\u003e\r\n    Requirements\r\n\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Good level of written and spoken English\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Strong HTML5 and CSS3 competence\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Excellent PHP7 skills, good with object oriented programming\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Good skills with native JavaScript, without frameworks and/or external\r\n        libraries\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Good understanding of website performance, both back- and front-end\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Able to work with Git version control\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Basic understanding of SEO\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Basic skills in Photoshop\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Able to troubleshoot problems with both macOS and Windows operating\r\n        systems\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Up to date knowledge of industry’s software and technology\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Professional time and deadline management\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003ch3\u003e\r\n\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003ch3\u003e\r\n    Beneficial\r\n\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Finnish language\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Experience with JavaScript front-end frameworks\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Understanding of relational databases (MySQL/MariaDB) and Linux server\r\n        platforms\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Experience in WordPress publishing system\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Experience in GitHub and advanced Git features, like submodules\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Experience in own projects and source code projects\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Willing to learn and genuine interest in personal growth\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Previous work experience in iGaming or equivalent industry\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Knowledge of casino games or industry\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003ch3\u003e\r\n\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003ch3\u003e\r\n    How to apply\r\n\u003c/h3\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Application period ends 15.4.2017. However, we will fill the position as\r\n    soon as we find a good candidate.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Send your application and CV to toni@goodgameltd.com.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Attach a portfolio of projects you have been involved in, if any.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Email subject field should read: “Web Developer”\r\n\u003c/p\u003e",
