    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003ca name="_GoBack"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003e\r\n        Do you want to be part of transforming lives of people working in more\r\n        then 100.000 companies through machine learning and at the same time,\r\n        you have a passion of becoming an expert in the field? Our innovative\r\n        software development team is looking to hire a summer trainees in the\r\n        field of machine learning to work with our family of developers,\r\n        testers, UX designers and domain experts\r\n    \u003c/em\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eMachine Learning Software Developer (summer trainee)\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    You will be working with the designing, developing and testing machine\r\n    learning solutions to automate processes in our financial management\r\n    software Procountor. You will be part of a Scrum team surrounded by skilled\r\n    colleagues.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Our core codebase is mostly written in Java, and we use the open-source\r\n    Vaadin framework for providing a beautiful front-end to the end-user. Other\r\n    key technologies include MySQL, JUnit, Jenkins, Kubernetes, Docker, Ansible\r\n    and Git. For mobile development, we use a modern JavaScript stack with\r\n    React. You can also have a look at our current public APIs by visiting\r\n    dev.procountor.com\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eKeys to success\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Understanding of artificial neural networks in the context of\r\n            supervised learning\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Basic understanding of forward and backward propagation\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Understanding the basics of fully connected, convolutional and\r\n            recurrent neural networks\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Experience in at least one programming language\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Experience with at least one distributed version control system\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Fluency with Finnish and/or English\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Eagerness to learn more\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    We also value\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Implementation knowledge in any commonly used machine learning\r\n            framework\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Knowledge of other methods used in supervised learning\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Knowledge in unsupervised learning\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Knowledge of accounting / financial management\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Knowledge of Scrum methodologies\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Experience with Python\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Experience with software development\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Experience with database and/or file systems\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \u003cp\u003e\r\n            Experience with cloud services\r\n        \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    You are self-imposed and have a solution-focused attitude. You take\r\n    responsibility of your own work and work well in teams. You don’t hesitate\r\n    to ask for help or to help others. As a team member you are friendly and\r\n    fun to work with.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eInterested?\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Send a CV and motivation letter to us as soon as possible, but no later\r\n    than Sun 20.1.2019. The employment starts upon agreement at the latest on\r\n    June and the position is full-time. We hope you can also continue working\r\n    with us part-time after your studies start in autumn.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Our office is located in Keilaranta, Espoo.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eWhy come and work for us?\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    We believe that motivated and happy people are the main ingredient in our\r\n    success story. We have built ourselves an environment that supports\r\n    wellbeing at work, professional development and work-life balance. We offer\r\n    for example flexible working hours, good working ergonomics and benefits of\r\n    sport and recreation. Additionally, we hold many events every year,\r\n    including sports, culture and other bigger or smaller occasions for\r\n    celebration. Fast growing company with international endeavors provides\r\n    good opportunities for professional learning and career development. Our\r\n    recently renovated office is very pleasant environment to spend your days\r\n    working.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003e\r\n        Accountor Finago is a Nordic provider of financial management services.\r\n        Our cloud-based solutions, Procountor and Tikon, serve over 120 000\r\n        companies and 1 400 accounting offices in Finland, Sweden, Norway and\r\n        Denmark. We are also market leaders in the field of financial\r\n        management. Overall, we employ nearly 300 experts in for example\r\n        financial management, software development and sales.\r\n    \u003c/em\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003eAccountor Finago is a part of Accountor Group.\u003c/em\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003ca\u003ehttps://accountor.emply.net/recruitment/vacancyApply.aspx?publishingId=13036b6e-f0b1-4e6b-8a8e-31976a15ab82\u0026languageKey=en-GB\u003c/a\u003e',
