    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    User interfaces research group at Aalto \r\n\u003ca href="http://userinterfaces.aalto.fi/" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank"\u003e\r\n    http://userinterfaces.aalto.fi/\r\n\u003c/a\u003e\r\n    is looking for potential research assistants. The post will start in the\r\n    fall of 2017 (e.g., September or October), and will be a part-time\r\n    contract (max 49% of full-time).\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    This is not yet an official job posting, but a survey of interested candidates.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Candidates are expected to fulfil some (not all) of the following\r\n    requirements:\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n  \u003cli\u003ecognitive modelling\u003c/li\u003e\r\n  \u003cli\u003emachine learning, e.g., reinforcement learning, POMDP \u003c/li\u003e\r\n  \u003cli\u003eprogramming skills (Python, Lisp)\u003c/li\u003e\r\n  \u003cli\u003econducting laboratory and/or field experiments with users\u003c/li\u003e\r\n  \u003cli\u003edata analysis with R\u003c/li\u003e\r\n  \u003cli\u003euser interface design / implementation of mobile user interfaces (with Java)\u003c/li\u003e\r\n  \u003cli\u003einterest in models of emotion\u003c/li\u003e\r\n  \u003cli\u003einterest in models of individual differences\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    If you find some of your skills and/or interests listed above, and are interested to work in an internationally strong research group in human-computer interaction, please contact\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003ca href="mailto:jussi.jokinen@aalto.fi"\u003ejussi.jokinen@aalto.fi\u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    with an open letter of interest and a CV.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
