    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\nA SC5 Full Stack Developer is a software pro with skills to build a complete business application. As a core\r\n\r\nmember of our client team, you will be creating effective electronic customer service and distribution\r\n\r\nchannels, information services, online stores and applications for the industrial internet.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n\r\nYou know how to build new digital services from scratch when you are not integrating them seamlessly into\r\n\r\nclients’ already existing back-end systems. You have strong experience in different back-end and front-end\r\n\r\ntechnologies and the will to show off your skills. We hope that you are experienced especially with\r\n\r\nJavaScript and want to take your skills to guru level with us.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003eYou value the quality of visual and algorithmic code. If needed you are able to make smart compromises for\r\n\r\nour client’s benefit, but avoid taking technical debt in your software projects.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nMost importantly you are eager to become an even better software professional.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n#NodeJS #JavaScript #React\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\r\nBecome a SC5er\u003cstrong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nWe promise that with SC5 you’ll get to jump into a great working culture with truly awesome people. With\r\n\r\nus you won’t get bored as we have varying business cases to offer, but also have different kinds of extra-\r\n\r\ncurricular activities such as an active climbing club, doodlers, a floorball team. We also do a lot of cool stuff\r\n\r\nin during working time, including but not limited to coffee tastings, Friday buns (sometimes bottles as well),\r\n\r\nyoga and afternoon break gymnastics. And of course, we welcome new clubs and activities open heartedly\r\n\r\nif you have anything on your mind!\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n\r\nWith meaningful work, we also offer among other things liberty and responsibility, the opportunity to hear\r\n\r\nand learn new things in seminars and conferences – even outside Finland – a wide array of perks that are\r\n\r\nhard to match and a competitive salary. Read more about what we have to offer from our \u003ca href="https://sc5.io/careers/"\u003ecareer pages\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nThis position can be situated in Kamppi, Helsinki or in our Jyväskylä site as well, depending on your location.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e We’d love to hear from you!\u003cstrong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, contact our PeopleOps Specialist, Aini Leppäkorpi +358 44 554 7756 /\r\n\r\naini@sc5.io, who’ll be more than happy to talk to you (preferably between office hours, but you can always\r\n\r\ntxt message, whatsapp, snap, tweet or email Aini). If all’s clear and you feel that SC5 and you could be a\r\n\r\nmatch then just send us your application by clicking the link and filling the short form and we’ll get back to\r\n\r\nyou.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n\r\nPlease apply before 31.7.2017 and note that we will start conducting interviews before the last applying\r\n\r\ndate.\u003c/p\u003e',
