    description:
      "\u003cp\u003e\r\n    University of Helsinki is seeking a programmer with expertise in\r\n    bio-informatics and user interface development.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Tasks will include further development of modules and implementation of a\r\n    Windows-based RNA virus identification program (VirusDetect) with visual\r\n    user interface. Earlier versions of the program exist for Linux environment\r\n    implemented mostly in Perl, Java, and R.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    A successful candidate has experience in bio-informatics (particularly\r\n    sequence assembly), sequence similarity searching and statistical analysis\r\n    thereof. Next-generation sequencing is the standard procedure for\r\n    generating data. Furthermore, the candidate is expected to develop user\r\n    interfaces and improve database management. Development of easy to\r\n    interpret visual representations of the analysis results, such as genome\r\n    coverage and depth, and relationship to other organisms, is expected.\r\n    Experience in programming languages suitable for the tasks, as well as\r\n    database management experience, are required. Knowledge of molecular\r\n    virology is considered a benefit.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Studies are carried out in collaboration with the International Potato\r\n    Center (CIP) and the International Institute for Tropical Agriculture\r\n    (IITA). The work can lead to a Master’s thesis supervised by Professors\r\n    Jari Valkonen and Veli Mäkinen.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Contact: jari.valkonen@helsinki.fi\r\n\u003c/p\u003e",
