    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Multiple teams, working with DevOps and automation development, in the\r\n    Service Operations department of Elisa Software Services are now looking\r\n    for enthusiastic \u003cstrong\u003eSoftware Developer Summer Trainees \u003c/strong\u003eto\r\n    join.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We offer various different roles within software development and we\r\n    guarantee a diverse and interesting tasks. You will be a trusted team\r\n    member and we have full trust on your work. Of course you’ll have Senior\r\n    colleagues to support you. Teams use agile methods in close co-operation\r\n    with business and other teams in Elisa.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    This role will offer you an opportunity to be part of building Elisa into a\r\n    top-class software house! You\'ll have the chance to develop your own skills\r\n    in a flexible and energetic work atmosphere with nice and experienced\r\n    colleagues. You will have caring leaders, opportunity to learn, modern\r\n    tools and flexible work culture. Your work will be challenging and\r\n    interesting! We have been listed as a\r\n    \u003cem\u003e\r\n        \u003ca\r\n            href="https://corporate.elisa.com/careers/tutustu_meihin/great-place-to-work/"\r\n        \u003e\r\n            Great Place to Work\r\n        \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    \u003c/em\u003e\r\n    – our environment is tested to be superb!\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003e\r\n        After the internship there is also a good chance to continue your\r\n        career with us as a full-time or part-time software engineer.\r\n    \u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    In order for us to find the best and most suitable task for you, we ask you\r\n    to let us know about your specific interests, wishes and skills in your\r\n    application. We hope you are familiar with at least some of these:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003e\r\n        Agile software development methods, React, Python, Kotlin, Java,\r\n        JavaScript, Ansible, Kubernetes, Kafka, OpenShift, Git\r\n    \u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003e\r\n        \u003cstrong\u003e\r\n            Apply now! We will start the interviews after 17th February.\r\n        \u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003c/em\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Please note: A legitimate security clearance will be made for the chosen\r\n    candidates.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003ca\r\n        href="https://corporate.elisa.fi/rest/corporate.elisa.fi/recruitment/openjobs/Kes%C3%A4ty%C3%B6SummerJob:SoftwareDeveloperTrainee(Helsinki)/fi/1400"\r\n    \u003e\r\n        Link to application page\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n',
