    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Our Research group at the Computer Science Department, University of Helsinki, has an immediate opening for:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    - a Master\'s-level (or advanced Bachelor\'s-level) or student,\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - 20-30 hours per week (flexible),\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - over the next 3-4 months, further continuation possible.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The student should be comfortable with:\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - Javascript/jQuery, HTML5, CSS,\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - mongoDB,\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - python and flask.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The candidate does not need to be a top-level expert in these, but s/he should be quite comfortable working with these. For example, s/he should be able to show some prior experience -- such as work or class projects.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    An interest in *language applications* or in *machine learning* is definitely a plus, but it is not a requirement -- someone who likes database \u0026amp; front-end work is also welcome.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    To see what the work is about, please visit the project page: \u003ca href="http://revita.cs.helsinki.fi/"\u003erevita.cs.helsinki.fi\u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The candidate should enjoy learning new things and working with other  people. Salary proportional to level of studies completed, according to University pay scales.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Interested persons should contact Dr Roman Yangarber at \u003ca href="mailto:firstname.lastname@cs.helsinki.fi"\u003e\r\n    firstname.lastname@cs.helsinki.fi\r\n\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e',
