    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Do you want to create something new? We are ramping up robotic process\r\n    automation capability from scratch and looking for two innovative IT\r\n    trainees to join our Digital Office team.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We are looking for two robotic process automation developers to join our\r\n    team on a green field project. Your main responsibility is to design,\r\n    develop, test and deploy automation solutions into production for our\r\n    internal tasks and processes. You will work in close co-operation with our\r\n    internal business, development and operations teams.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Basware Digital Office enables Basware day-to-day business success through\r\n    provision of robust, scalable and modular IT Solutions, Services and\r\n    processes. It is also responsible of driving cross-company projects and\r\n    programs aiming to enable Digitalization in Basware.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eWhat we’re looking for:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \r\n            Programming and software engineering skills \u0026amp; passion -PLEASE,\r\n            show examples of your skills \u0026amp; projects in your application\r\n        \r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \r\n            Studies in relevant field (Information technology, computer science\r\n            business administration)\r\n        \r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \r\n            Agile development knowledge\r\n        \r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \r\n            Fluent in spoken and written English\r\n        \r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \r\n            Hands on experience from \u003cu\u003emore than one of following items\u003c/u\u003e:\r\n        \r\n        \r\n            \u003cli\u003e\r\n                    \u003ca name="_GoBack"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\r\n                    JIRA and Confluence, Git, QlikView, BMC Remedy, UiPath,\r\n                    Blue Prism, Splunk, SQL, Linux, Windows servers, .NET and\r\n                    C#, Java, Python, Dynamics CRM, Amazon Web service,\r\n                    Microsoft Azure, Scaled Agile Framework (Safe)\r\n                \r\n            \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \r\n    \r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Personal\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \r\n            Team player and good communication skills\r\n        \r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \r\n            You are Results-driven and able to prioritize efficiently\r\n        \r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \r\n            Good problems solving skills and capability see big picture\r\n        \r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \r\n            Practical and get things done approach to work\r\n        \r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Other preferred skills:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \r\n            Work experience in IT fields and especially previous robotic\r\n            process automation experience\r\n        \r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        \r\n            Knowledge of AI, Machine learning, R or intelligent cloud services\r\n        \r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You can be just Finishing your studies or recently graduated. We don\'t\r\n    expect you to be seasoned expert of robotics, but instead an excited junior\r\n    with creative ideas and new approaches to the field. Since software\r\n    robotics is a new discipline, you should be open minded and eager to learn\r\n    and experiment.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eWhy you’ll love working at Basware:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    At Basware, you’ll get to leave your mark and make a real difference on our\r\n    products. You’ll be part of a motivated, tech-savvy and friendly team that\r\n    delivers world-class products for hundreds of companies globally. We\r\n    believe in giving you the freedom to deliver your best work: that’s why\r\n    we’re flexible around hours, tools and working methods. Our ways of working\r\n    are truly global: as part of our technical personnel, you’ll often work in\r\n    a global virtual team with colleagues across the world. With us, you can\r\n    build your career at an international, forward-thinking and profitable\r\n    company.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eThe details:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Location: Espoo, Finland\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Position: Full-time fixed term for 6 months\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Send us your application by 29th October 2017. PLEASE showcase any related\r\n    projects (school or hobby), Hackathons, Github profile, code samples etc.\r\n    -candidates with examples to show will be prioritized!\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eFurther information\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    If you have any questions, you can get in touch with Marko Lähde, Senior Solution Manager\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    marko.lahde@basware.com\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eAbout us\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Basware is the global leader in providing purchase to pay and e-invoicing\r\n    solutions. Over a million users globally, across industries in both the\r\n    private and public sectors, rely on Basware products to automate\r\nbusiness-critical financial processes. Find out more at    \u003ca href="http://www.basware.com/"\u003ewww.basware.com\u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
