    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The Genome-scale algorithmics research group (\r\n\u003ca href="http://www.helsinki.fi/genome-scale-algorithmics"\r\n    rel="noreferrer"\r\n    target="_blank"\r\n\u003e\r\n    http://www.helsinki.fi/\r\n    \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n        genome-scale-algorithmics\r\n    \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n\u003c/a\u003e\r\n    ) is searching for a research assistant to work on her/his Master\'s thesis\r\n    related to the project "Sequence analysis revisited and extended".\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The topic of the thesis is exploration and evaluation of techniques for\r\n    finding maximal exact matches between a sequence and a labeled directed\r\n    acyclic graph. The area is under active development, and there is a\r\n    possibility for novel findings during the project. Implementation and\r\n    experimentation of possible new approaches against existing tools is part\r\n    of the project. The expected outcome of the thesis work is an efficient\r\n    preprocessing step that will be used together with other members of the\r\n    research group in pan-genomics and transcriptomics applications.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The position is available either as a part-time or a full-time position,\r\n    for a duration between 1/2-1 year. Salary is dependent on the level of\r\n    studies completed.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You are a suitable candidate if you:\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eAre a Master\'s level student ready to start the thesis work\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eHave good general programming skills, especially in C++\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eAre able to communicate in English\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eAre interested in and master well at least some of the topics covered in\r\n    advanced courses on algorithms and data structures, string processing\r\n    algorithms, data compression techniques, biological sequence analysis, and\r\n    algorithms in molecular biology.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    For more information, please contact:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Veli Mäkinen (\u003ca href="mailto:veli.makinen@helsinki.fi"\u003eveli.makinen@helsinki.fi\u003c/a\u003e)\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
