    description:
      "\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Topic: Creating an online programming course about Qt.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The Qt Company is looking for a Master’s thesis student to work on creating\r\n    an online programming course on mooc.fi.\r\n    The work centres on creating the course content for a Qt programming course\r\n    and finalising the technical as aspects of\r\n    the software pieces needed for the course, that have been started as part\r\n    of a student project.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The course content will be based on learning material The Qt Company has\r\n    created for it’s professional learning services.\r\n    The material is not designed for online learning, but can be adapted for an\r\n    online course. This means that the student\r\n    does not need to have previous in-depth knowledge of Qt, but can\r\n    concentrate on the creation of the course.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The technical aspects of the work include working on the Qt Creator plugin\r\n    for interfacing with the Test My Code(TMC)\r\n    course server developed at the University of Helsinki\r\n    (https://github.com/testmycode/tmc-server). If there is need to edit\r\n    the TMC plugin that handles Qt code on the TMC server side, this will fall\r\n    under the work description.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eStarting date: as soon as possible\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eDuration: The thesis is assumed to take about six months of work.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eLocation: The Qt Company offices in Leppävaara, Espoo\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eObjectives: An online Qt programming course that has been tested on mooc.fi\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Required skills: Programming, preferably some experience of C++, and\r\n    interest in online courses\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Pay: The position is paid\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Contact and applications: Tero Kojo, tero.kojo@qt.io\r\n\u003c/p\u003e",
