    description:
      "\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The Qt Company is looking for a Master’s thesis student to work on\r\n    implementing a plugin to the Qt bugreports system\r\n    for interfacing with modern requirements engineering tools.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The Qt Company is responsible for the development of Qt, productization and\r\n    licensing under commercial and open-\r\n    source licenses. Qt is a C++ based framework of libraries and tools that\r\n    enables the development of powerful, interactive\r\n    and cross-platform applications and devices.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    This thesis however does not revolve around Qt itself. Qt is looking to\r\n    improve its requirements management process\r\n    with the help of modern tools and processes developed in the OpenReq\r\n    research project. As part of the project there is a\r\n    trial in which the tools from OpenReq need to be tested on real data. This\r\n    data comes from The Qt Company bugreports\r\n    database, which also contains requirements. This requires building a plugin\r\n    for JIRA, the tool we use for bugs and\r\n    requirements, and also someone to do the tests for the trial. This work\r\n    scope should be suitable for a Master’s thesis. As\r\n    the work is part of a larger project, there will be help available to bring\r\n    the thesis worker up to speed on how we use our\r\n    systems and help if necessary.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eStarting date: as soon as possible\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eDuration: The thesis is assumed to take about six months of work.\u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003eLocation: The Qt Company offices in Leppävaara, Espoo\u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Objectives: A working plugin for the Qt bugreports system which has been\r\n    successfully tested with the tools from the\r\n    OpenReq EU-project.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Required skills: the implementation language is Java, basic understanding\r\n    of requirements engineering, any experience of\r\n    JIRA is a benefit\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Pay: The position is paid\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Contact and applications: Tero Kojo, tero.kojo@qt.io\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Context: OpenReq (openreq.eu) is an EU Horizon 2020 framework project that\r\n    aims to provide better requirements\r\n    engineering to your organization. We are driving for improvements in the\r\n    areas of requirements identification,\r\n    classification and decision making support. The improvements we are looking\r\n    for can be achieved through improved\r\n    processes, methods and tools. OpenReq is also looking at hot topics like\r\n    Artificial Intelligence methods to help with\r\n    managing requirements and requirement extraction from natural language like\r\n    social media posts.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The project involves four academic partners: HITEC University of Hamburg\r\n    (GER), Universitat Politecnica de Catalunya\r\n    (ESP), Technical University of Graz (AUT), and University of Helsinki.\r\n    Other five industrial partners participate in OPENREQ:\r\n    The Qt Company (FIN), SIEMENS (AUT), ENG Engineering(ITA), vogella (GER),\r\n    and Wind Tre S.p.a. (ITA).\r\n\u003c/p\u003e",
