    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003e\r\n        Finnair is a network airline specialising in passenger and cargo\r\n        traffic between Asia and Europe. Helsinki’sgeographical location gives\r\n        Finnair a competitive advantage, since the fastest connections between\r\n        many European destinations and Asian megacities fly over Finland.\r\n        Finnair’s vision is to offer its passengers a unique Nordic experience,\r\n        and its mission is to offer the smoothest, fastest connections in the\r\n        northern hemisphere via Helsinki and the best network to the world from\r\n        its home markets. Finnair is the only Nordic carrier with a 4-star\r\n        Skytrax ranking and a member of the \u003cstrong\u003eone\u003c/strong\u003eworld alliance.\r\n        In 2016, Finnair’s revenues amounted to EUR 2,317 million and it had a\r\n        personnel of 4,940 at the year-end. Finnair Plc’s shares are quoted on\r\n        Nasdaq Helsinki.\r\n    \u003c/em\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003e\r\n        The heart of Finnair’s commercial activities is Revenue Management and\r\n        Pricing (RMP), which manages revenue in excess of EUR 2,000 million.\r\n        This function performs analysis and complex optimization to determine\r\n        what is the best possible price level and passenger mix on any route,\r\n        any flight, any day, any time of the year. Currently the demand\r\n        forecast is created on individual flight level, but in order to support\r\n        Finnair’s growth strategy and the expected increase in connecting\r\n        traffic flows in Helsinki hub, Finnair now invests in an\r\n        origin-destination based (O\u0026amp;D) revenue management system.\r\n        Implementing an origin-destination based system will add more\r\n        dimensionality to the demand forecasting and optimization functions,\r\n        and therefore Finnair is looking for skilled resources to complement\r\n        the current team of Revenue Management professionals.\r\n    \u003c/em\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    In order to support growth, we are now looking for sharp and\r\n    business-minded\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eDEMAND ANALYSTS AND INVENTORY ANALYSTS\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nto strengthen our team of Revenue Management and Pricing (RMP) experts.    \u003cu\u003e\u003c/u\u003e\u003cu\u003e\u003c/u\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003eIn Demand Analyst role\u003c/em\u003e\r\n    , you are responsible for maximizing network revenue through demand\r\n    forecasting practices for your appointed markets. In this role you monitor\r\n    and influence passenger demand forecasts ensuring they reflect the current\r\n    competitive environment, commercial strategy, booking trends, market\r\n    conditions, operating schedule, special events and seasonal demand\r\n    variations. As demand analyst you generate insights on passenger demand in\r\n    co-operation with various stakeholders such as global sales, pricing and\r\n    inventory management.\u003cu\u003e\u003c/u\u003e\u003cu\u003e\u003c/u\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003eIn Inventory Analyst role,\u003c/em\u003e\r\n    you will regularly review and monitor flight and route performance and\r\n    manage flights and capacity over the life cycle of the flight. Your primary\r\n    objective will be to maximize the revenue for each flight in the schedule\r\n    by managing for instance overbooking, short-term capacity adjustments and\r\n    tour operator allotments. To do this, you will apply inventory management\r\n    best practices and utilize revenue management tools.\u003cu\u003e\u003c/u\u003e\u003cu\u003e\u003c/u\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    For both roles, we are looking for goal-oriented people with analytical\r\n    skills and true business-orientation who are ready to take responsibility\r\n    for delivering the revenue budget and targets associated with their\r\n    portfolio.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eOur expectations towards you:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    - Excellent analytical skills and experience with well-versed\r\n    decision-making capabilities\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - Demonstrated commercial and strategic thinking and related experience\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - Ability to analyze, interpret and present large volumes of data\r\n    \u003cs\u003e\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003c/s\u003e\r\n    - A self-starter attitude\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - Effective communication skills and ability to describe complex systems\r\n    and strategies in an easy to understand manner\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - Enthusiasm to get involved in and lead projects as needed\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - Strong team-player\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - Well-developed prioritization and time planning skills with excellent\r\n    attention to detail\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - Fluent English both written and verbal\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    - Master’s degree or equivalent in economics, business, aviation or\r\n    similar.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We offer you an exciting opportunity in the multifaceted, fast changing\r\n    aviation and travel industry. This is a great time to join the Finnair and\r\n    contribute to our growth journey. Here at Finnair ambitious, competent and\r\n    motivated people can really make a difference.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Want to join? Fill in the application form, attaching your CV, cover letter\r\n    and salary request by December 15\u003csup\u003eth\u003c/sup\u003e, 2017 at\r\n    \u003ca href="http://www.finnair.com/jobs" target="_blank"\u003e\r\n        www.finnair.com/jobs\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    . For more information, please contact Mika Stirkkinen, VP, Revenue\r\n    Management \u0026amp; Pricing by phone\r\n    \u003ca href="tel:+358%2040%205588520" value="+358405588520" target="_blank"\u003e\r\n        +358 40 558 8520\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    on December 4 between 3 pm and 5 pm and on Dec 8 between 10 am and 12 am.\r\nYou can also send your question to    \u003ca href="mailto:jobs@finnair.com" target="_blank"\u003ejobs@finnair.com\u003c/a\u003e.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
