    description:
      '\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    Summer trainee at FMI: AI and satellite observations of greenhouse gases, Helsinki\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Are you looking for a summer job in science and research? Are you\r\n        interested to test your own research skills and work in highly\r\n        stimulating scientific environment? Do you know that AI is the new\r\n        black?\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n        The Greenhouse Gases and Satellite Methods group at Finnish\r\n        Meteorological Institute is looking for highly motivated person with\r\n        passion for science and interest in atmospheric observations and\r\n        artificial intelligence. In this project, we will use space-borne\r\n        greenhouse gas observations together with mathematical, statistical and\r\n        computational methods. The aim is to separate the contributions of\r\n        anthropogenic sources and natural sinks and to quantify uncertainties\r\n        related to these data-driven estimates, which are needed to support the\r\n        international efforts to restrict the greenhouse gas emissions and are\r\n        crucial for future climate projections.\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n        Applicant should have a background in computer science, engineering,\r\n        physics or mathematics. In particular we are looking for candidates who\r\n        have good knowledge on AI methods. If you think you are suitable for\r\n        this position we encourage you to apply!\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n        Send your application (cover letter, CV and a list of exams and grades)\r\n        to kesatyot.kirjaamo@fmi.fi, cc janne.hakkarainen@fmi.fi\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n        (Internship)\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        \u003cstrong\u003eTime and duration:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n        1.6.2018 – 31.8.2018 (negotiable)\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        \u003cstrong\u003eForm of employment:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n        Summer job\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        \u003cstrong\u003eSalary:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n        1650 € per month\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        \u003cstrong\u003eHow many interns?:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n        1\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        \u003cstrong\u003e\r\n            Additional information on the salary or other recompense:\r\n        \u003c/strong\u003e\r\n        1650 € per month\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        \u003cstrong\u003eLocation:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n        Helsinki Metropolitan Area\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        \u003cstrong\u003eApplication deadline:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n        31.01.2018\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Finnish or Swedish language skills are not required for this position\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        \u003cstrong\u003eChoose field(s) of study:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n        Mathematics and Statistics, Other Natural Sciences, Other Technology\r\n        Sciences\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    EMPLOYER INFORMATION\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cstrong\u003eFinnish Meteorological Institute\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Erik Palménin aukio 1\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    FI-00560 HELSINKI\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003ca href="http://ikaweb.fmi.fi" target="_blank"\u003ehttp://ikaweb.fmi.fi\u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Janne Hakkarainen\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n   p. +358 45 124 0257\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n',
