    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Summer trainee at FMI: Monitoring air pollution using satellite\r\n    observations\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Are you looking for a summer job in science and research? Are you\r\n    interested to test your own research skills and work in highly stimulating\r\n    scientific environment? Do you want to learn about new high resolution\r\n    satellite observations for monitoring air pollution?\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    The Atmospheric Remote Sensing group at Finnish Meteorological Institute is\r\n    looking for highly motivated person with passion for science and interest\r\n    in atmospheric observations and their application for air pollution\r\n    monitoring. In this project, we will use space-borne observations of\r\n    short-lived atmospheric gases (nitrogen dioxide and sulfur dioxide) to map\r\n    air pollution levels in Finland and on global scale. The plan is to analyze\r\n    new atmospheric observations from ESA’s Sentinel 5 Precursor satellite\r\n    together with ground- based measurements. The aim is to map and apply these\r\n    observations to monitor different source of pollution in Finland and abroad\r\n    (e.g., refineries, metal smelters, shipping, car traffic, power plants).\r\n    This work will provide useful information for companies and decision makers\r\n    (cleantech and energy sector, urban and environmental authorities).\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Applicant should have a background in computer science, engineering,\r\n    physics or mathematics. In particular we are looking for candidates who\r\n    have good knowledge on programming and data visualisation/mapping (Matlab\r\n    preferred). If you think you are suitable for this position we encourage\r\n    you to apply sending a 1 page cover letter, an updated CV and a list of\r\n    your exams and grades.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\nSend your applications to\u003ca href="mailto:kesatyot.kirjaamo@fmi.fi"\u003ekesatyot.kirjaamo@fmi.fi\u003c/a\u003e, cc    \u003ca href="mailto:iolanda.ialongo@fmi.fi"\u003eiolanda.ialongo@fmi.fi\u003c/a\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Time and duration: 1.6.2018 – 31.8.2018 (negotiable)\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Form of employment: Summer job Salary: 1600 eur / month\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    How many interns?: 1\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Additional information on the salary or other recompense: 1600 eur / month\r\n    (5 days holiday)\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Location: Helsinki Metropolitan Area Application deadline: 31.01.2018\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Finnish or Swedish language skills are not required for this position\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Choose Universities: All universities\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Choose field(s) of study: Mathematics and Statistics, Other Natural\r\n    Sciences, Other Technology Sciences\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    EMPLOYER INFORMATION\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Finnish Meteorological Institute\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Erik Palménin aukio 1, 00560 Helsinki\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href="http://blog.fmi.fi" target="_blank"\u003eblog.fmi.fi\u003c/a\u003e\r\n    \\ILMApilot\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    Iolanda Ialongo\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    p.\r\n    \u003ca href="tel:%2B358%2044%200112140" value="+358440112140"\u003e\r\n        +358 44 0112140\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    \u003ca href="mailto:Aiolanda.ialongo@fmi.fi"\u003e\r\n        email:iolanda.ialongo@fmi.fi\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n',
