    description:
      '\u003csection\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                \u003cdiv id="job-desc"\u003e\r\n                    \u003cp\u003e\r\n                        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n                        Are you interested in a challenging job where you get\r\n                        to learn from the best within a field you choose?\r\n                    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n                    \u003cp\u003e\r\n                        Elisa\'s Software Services department is looking for\r\n                        recent or near-future graduates for summer\r\n                        traineeships. (Warning: most of our summer trainees\r\n                        have stayed on board with us ever since, so you might\r\n                        not want to leave ever again.)\r\n                        \u003cstrong\u003e\r\n                            We offer various different roles within software\r\n                            development - it\'s up to you to pick what you want\r\n                            to do.\r\n                        \u003c/strong\u003e\r\n                        Whichever role you choose, we guarantee a diverse job\r\n                        and a steep learning curve. You will join a team of\r\n                        experienced, humble professionals and get to develop\r\n                        interesting services. As you gain in experience and\r\n                        competence, you will have the opportunity to transfer\r\n                        to new, more challenging development positions.\r\n                    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n                    \u003cp\u003e\r\n                        As a summer trainee in Software Services, you can focus\r\n                        on e.g. front-end or back-end development, DevOps, test\r\n                        automation or 3D web development. In order for us to\r\n                        find the best and most suitable task for you among\r\n                        these alternatives,\r\n                        \u003cstrong\u003e\r\n                            we ask you to let us know about your specific\r\n                            interests, wishes and skills in your application.\r\n                        \u003c/strong\u003e\r\n                    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n                    \u003cp\u003e\r\n                        In order to succeed in your job, we require you to have\r\n                        a strong desire for achievement within a challenging,\r\n                        diverse environment. Operating in this position\r\n                        requires written and spoken fluency in English. Finnish\r\n                        skills are not required. The ability to work as part of\r\n                        a group is a prerequisite for success and requires an\r\n                        active, responsible grip on work and good initiative.\r\n                        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n                    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n                    \u003cp\u003e\r\n                        We expect you to be inspired and motivated at work. You\r\n                        do not shy away from challenges or operating outside\r\n                        your comfort zone – you actively seek out such\r\n                        situations. Open communication and an active approach\r\n                        are important when you are working with different\r\n                        stakeholders. A strong ability to plan and make\r\n                        decisions independently is necessary, as well as to\r\n                        operate in a changing, dynamic environment in\r\n                        cooperation with the technical and commercial\r\n                        organisation.\r\n                    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n                    \u003cp\u003e\r\n                        In your application, tell us which one(s) of the\r\n                        following you have experience in:\r\n                        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n                        \u003cem\u003e\r\n                            Agile software development methods, React, Java,\r\n                            JavaScript, HTML, HTML5, Python, REST, SQL,\r\n                            Ansible, Kubernetes, OpenShift, Jenkins, Git,\r\n                        \u003c/em\u003e\r\n                        \u003cem\u003ewebGL, BabylonJS\u003c/em\u003e\r\n                        .\r\n                    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n                    \u003cp\u003e\r\n                        You will be based in our incredibly cool HQ in Pasila,\r\n                        Helsinki.\r\n                        \u003ca\r\n                            href="http://corporate.elisa.com/careers/avoimet_tyopaikat/careers-ohjelmistotyo-ja-it/"\r\n                            target="_blank"\r\n                        \u003e\r\n                            Read more about Elisa and why we love working here.\r\n                        \u003c/a\u003e\r\n                    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n                    \u003cp\u003e\r\n                        Got questions? Feel free to reach out to Otso at\r\n                        otso.palonen@elisa.fi.\r\n                    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n                    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                        \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n                            \u003ca\r\n                                href="https://elisa.rekrytointi.com/paikat/?o=A_RJ\u0026amp;jgid=1\u0026amp;jid=667"\r\n                            \u003e\r\n                                TÄYTÄ HAKEMUS\r\n                            \u003c/a\u003e\r\n                        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n                    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n                \u003c/div\u003e\r\n            \u003c/div\u003e\r\n        \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003c/section\u003e\r\n\u003csection\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003c/section\u003e',
