    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We are now looking for NAPCON Trainees to our offices in Porvoo, Turku and\r\n    Espoo.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You will participate in the delivery and development of NAPCON to improve\r\n    plant safety, productivity and quality. Our NAPCON solutions are\r\n    proprietary Advanced Process Control (APC), Dynamic Real-time Optimization\r\n    (DRTO), Real-time Process Information products, Operator Training\r\n    Simulators and Educational Games. See www.napconsuite.com for more insight,\r\n    information and inspiration about NAPCON.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Depending on your skills and your educational background tasks to be\r\n    performed together with us range from software development, game\r\n    development and implementation of process design within our trainings\r\n    simulators to assisting our staff in delivering APC and/or Operator\r\n    Training Simulators for the process industry.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Our expectations\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You are a University student with focus on e.g. one of these:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Information Technology or Computer Science\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Process, Chemical or Energy Engineering\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Automation Technology\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Project management\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    You have some knowledge in one or more of these fields:\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Modern software development environments and programming languages such\r\n        as C# .NET, C++, Java, HTML5, and JavaScript\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Data science, such as Artificial Intelligence\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Agile project management practices\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Process modeling or flow simulation (CFD)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Control design\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We offer you an interesting and challenging role in an international and\r\n    dynamic environment, in a company that is always expanding and seeking new\r\n    solutions for its clients and other stakeholders. We offer you the\r\n    opportunity to use and enlarge your expertise, working together with the\r\n    top experts in the field.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We offer flexibility regarding the vacancy start date depending on the\r\n    schedule of your studies, and the employment can begin during April, May or\r\n    June, 2018.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    The person selected for the position must pass a health examination that\r\n    includes a drug test.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    To apply\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Submit your application by 28th February, 2018 at our career portal\r\n    \u003ca href="https://career5.successfactors.eu/career?company=C0008491343P"\u003ehere\u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Please use "NAPCON" as keywords and "Summer intership" as Job Area. Please\r\n    attach a Cover Letter, CV and Transcript of Studies on your application.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n    Neste Jacobs name has changed 1 January 2018 and we are now Neste\r\n    Engineering Solutions. Please find further information of our business and\r\n    projects \u003ca href="www.nestejacobs.com"\u003e here\u003c/a\u003e.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
