    description:
      '\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003e\r\n        Neomore was founded in 2006 as a SAP consulting company, and our\r\n        business idea is straightforward: we aim to support our customers’\r\n        business using SAP technologies. In practice this means that we design,\r\n        build and maintain the SAP software that is often vital to our\r\n        customers’ business operations.\r\n    \u003c/em\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    When applications are built for customers to get all the potential power\r\n    and use out of their SAP-systems, often additional plugins or customized\r\n    properties are added to existing systems. When the goal is to make the\r\n    client’s SAP more usable, also the created additional applications have to\r\n    be responsive, intuitive and indeed, usable. In both of these roles you\r\n    will create and/or design user interfaces to meet customers’ diverse needs\r\n    in a user-friendly and functional way.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    Both of these roles can be altered according to your prior experience and\r\n    interests; you can be an experienced developer or designer, or this can be\r\n    a great opportunity for a budding UI superstar to blossom.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cstrong\u003eFrom the next Frontend Developer we expect:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Ability to create (and learn more about creating) beautiful interfaces\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Applicable knowledge of Web UI -technologies (HTML, CSS)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Some knowledge of JavaScript (extra points for React-skills)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Some work experience (for instance from a summer job – relevant work\r\n        experience is considered as a big plus)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Good skills in English (plus points for also knowing some Finnish)\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv dir="ltr"\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        \u003cstrong\u003eFrom the next UI/UX Designer we expect:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n        \u003cul\u003e\r\n            \u003cli\u003e\r\n                Ability to design (and learn more about designing) beautiful\r\n                interfaces\r\n            \u003c/li\u003e\r\n            \u003cli\u003e\r\n                Knowledge of Web UI -technologies (HTML, CSS)\r\n            \u003c/li\u003e\r\n            \u003cli\u003e\r\n                Knowledge of some relevant design platform (for instance\r\n                InVision, Adobe…)\r\n            \u003c/li\u003e\r\n            \u003cli\u003e\r\n                Some work experience (for instance from a summer job – relevant\r\n                work experience is considered as a big plus)\r\n            \u003c/li\u003e\r\n            \u003cli\u003e\r\n                Good skills in English (plus points for also knowing some\r\n                Finnish)\r\n            \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eSkill tags: JavaScript, HTML, CSS\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eRead more and apply by the 19th of June\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    :\r\n    \u003ca\r\n        href="https://atalent.fi/open-position/junior-frontend-developer-junior-ui-ux-designer"\r\n        target="_blank"\r\n    \u003e\r\n        https://atalent.fi/open-\r\n        \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n            position/junior-frontend-\r\n            \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n                developer-junior-ui-ux-\r\n                \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n                    designer\r\n                \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n            \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n        \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n',
