    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\nAre you interested in developing AI and machine\tlearning techniques for the space industry? Do you\r\nlike the idea of flexible work in a small highly skilled team?\r\nLearn\tAI\tby\tdoing - help us solve one of the biggest bottlenecks in the development of complex\r\nengineering systems!\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e \u003cb\u003eCompany description:\u003c/b\u003e\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nSelko Technologies is a venture capitalist backed AI company focusing on automating the analysis of textbased\r\ndata in complex, large scale engineering projects. Our mission is to streamline the collection and\r\nanalysis of written technical requirements, and help catch issues in early stage systems engineering.\r\nComplex systems such as space crafts, satellites, airplanes or nuclear power plants can have tens of\r\nthousands of text requirements. Collecting requirements takes years of work efforts, and the massive\r\namount of requirements and their connections make requirements analysis cognitively close to impossible.\r\nOur tools save massive costs, cut down development time, and increase the quality of complex technical\r\nsystems.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nSelko Technologies reached top 10 in Slush 100 competition in November 2017, and secured VC funding in\r\nDecember 2017.\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nAs a Junior Data Scientist, you will be responsible for providing analytical solutions to problems in\r\nrequirements processing, analysis and visualisation. You will focus on using natural language processing\r\n(NLP), semantic analysis and machine learning techniques to research, develop and implement\r\nstatistical and predictive methods for the Selko SaaS tool. You are capable of independently organising\r\nand managing your work, but collaborate well with the team members as well as business and\r\ncustomer stakeholders. \r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nWe offer the opportunity of becoming an early team member in a growing startup, and an opportunity\r\nto work in an international team on an in-house SaaS product, solving a real customer pain. Selko is a\r\nsmall company where everyone\'s opinion and input is valuable, and over time you can evolve into a\r\ncentral role in the organisation. The work is flexible and the team members can work in the way that\r\nsuits them best. For exceptional recruits, also option programs can be negotiated.\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\n\u003cb\u003eWe are looking for: \u003c/b\u003e\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eM.Sc., master student, or Ph.D. student in computer science, physics, mathematics, statistics\r\nor related fields \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eStrong interest in AI, especially NLP and Machine-Learning \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eKnowledge of Python, R, Octave or equivalent \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with SQL and databases is considered a plus \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003cli\u003eGood communication and presentation skills in English \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003eTo apply please send a CV and covering letter to suvi.ellila@selko.io using the subject line "Data\r\nScientist Application". \r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n\u003cp\u003e\r\nCheck \u003ca href="http://selko.io"\u003e selko.io \u003c/a\u003e for further details, and for more information about the job and the recruitment\r\nprocess, please contact Suvi Ellilä, +358 50 329 1131, suvi.ellila@selko.io\r\n\u003c/p\u003e',
