    description:
      '\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003e\r\n        Navigil was founded in 2010. The acquisition of Fastrax’ track \u0026amp;\r\n        trace business in 2011 started the journey to become one of the leading\r\n        providers of wearable telecare products and services. Now Navigil is\r\n        one of the leading providers of wearable telecare products and services\r\n        in the world. Navigil offers its users quality of life and independence\r\n        – freedom to live safely at home. Also families and relatives enjoy\r\n        peace of mind thanks to features such as voice connection, emergency\r\n        call, fall detection as well as location and wellbeing information.\r\n        Both the user and society benefit (\r\n        \u003ca href="https://www.navigil.com/" target="_blank"\u003e\r\n            https://www.navigil.com/\r\n        \u003c/a\u003e\r\n        ).\r\n    \u003c/em\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003e\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cem\u003e\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003c/em\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    Navigil is looking for a Frontend Developer who is ready to advance their\r\n    career and dive into the fascinating world of wearables and healthtech. We\r\n    aren’t looking for a ready-made guru – instead we seek somebody who really\r\n    wants to learn, develop and grow. This is why we don’t have an extremely\r\n    strict set of skills that you need to master for you to apply; the role has\r\n    room to be altered in the long run according to your knowledge and\r\n    preferences, and it can grow with you.\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    In the beginning your job will consist of developing a new dashboard with\r\n    modern web technologies that will replace an old PHP-based version. When a\r\n    MVP of the updated service is completed there will be room for developing\r\n    new features and updates.\r\n    \u003cem\u003e\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003c/em\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eWe expect:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cul\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Knowledge of software development (school, work or personal\r\n            projects)\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Knowledge of Web UI -technologies (HTML, CSS)\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Applicable skills in JavaScript (more specifically React)\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Interest to work in a startup environment in the rapidly evolving\r\n            wearable sector\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Good skills in English\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003e\r\n        Skill tags: JavaScript, React, HTML, CSS\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n        Read more and apply by the 16th of June\r\n    \u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    :\r\n    \u003ca\r\n        href="https://atalent.fi/open-position/junior-frontend-developer"\r\n        target="_blank"\r\n    \u003e\r\n        https://atalent.fi/open-\r\n        \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n            position/junior-frontend-\r\n            \u003cwbr\u003e\r\n                developer\r\n            \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n        \u003c/wbr\u003e\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n',
