    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\r\n    We are looking for a developer interested in developing his/her skills\r\n    further in the role of a Full-Stack Developer. We hope you are familiar\r\n    with at least some of the technologies of our stack but don’t expect you to\r\n    know everything. We also hope you are eager to dive deep in challenging\r\n    product development together with the team of experienced developers\r\n\u003c/p\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003cstrong\u003e\r\n    To get a good start and to excel in the job, we expect the following:\r\n\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cul\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            You code because that’s what you enjoy doing – you are used to\r\n            searching information and learning by doing. You are curious\r\n            towards new technologies and are eager to constantly get better as\r\n            a developer.\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Experience with Python – you’ve learnt at least the basics at your\r\n            university and have done some projects as a hobby or as part of\r\n            your studies/job.\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Experience with JavaScript – you are familiar with some of the\r\n            frameworks and are eager to work with React.\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Experience with SQL – basic understanding through university\r\n            courses/other projects is required\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Ability to work 30+ hours per week – more flexibility with the work\r\n            hours is possible during the year of 2018 if you are finishing up\r\n            your studies for example.\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Fluent English\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cstrong\u003eWe offer you:\u003c/strong\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cul\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            A chance to fully concentrate in long-term product development – no\r\n            “project-hopping”\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            In the long term, a chance to take part in the R\u0026amp;D of SSH’s\r\n            other products as well if you wish to broaden your view\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            Challenging problem solving with a globally significant product\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n        \u003cli\u003e\r\n            An international and professional work environment where you can be\r\n            as you are\r\n        \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003c/ul\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\nSounds like a match for you? Submit your application in PDF by    \u003cstrong\u003e6.8.2018\u003c/strong\u003e:\r\n    \u003ca\r\n        href="https://apply.atalent.fi/ssh-communications-security-full-stack-developer-7-2018"\r\n        target="_blank"\r\n        rel="noopener noreferrer"\r\n    \u003e\r\n        https://apply.atalent.fi/ssh-communications-security-full-stack-developer-7-2018\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    . Please mention your earliest possible starting date in your application\r\n    documents. We are very interested to hear more about the projects you’ve\r\n    done so far, so please include some samples of your work in your\r\n    application documents (Github or equivalent for example).\r\n\u003c/div\u003e',
