      "    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Elisa is actively seeking new opportunities and capabilities for\r\ntraditional database solutions. We are now looking for a        \u003cstrong\u003emaster's thesis worker\u003c/strong\u003e to build a view on existing\r\n        database solutions used by several different applications. More\r\n        importantly, we are expecting a future vision on a high quality and\r\n        cost-effective database environment.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        If you are studying e.g. computing or computer science, you have basic\r\n        knowledge on databases, you are interested in this area and you are\r\n        looking for a topic for your master's thesis, don't hesitate to contact\r\n        us. Fill out your contact information through the link below and we'll\r\n        get in touch and discuss more!\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        We expect you to work on your thesis full time, and we hope that you'd\r\n        be able to start already by the end of the summer. You will be fully\r\n        compensated for your work in line with the recommendations of TEK and\r\n        other unions' recommendations.\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n    \u003cp\u003e\r\n        Leave an application:\r\n        \u003ca\r\n            href=\"https://corporate.elisa.fi/rest/corporate.elisa.fi/recruitment/openjobs/Thesisworker(databasesolutions)/fi/1595\"\r\n            target=\"_blank\"\r\n        \u003e\r\n            https://corporate.elisa.fi/rest/corporate.elisa.fi/recruitment/openjobs/Thesisworker(databasesolutions)/fi/1595\r\n        \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    \u003c/p\u003e\r\n\r\n",
