    description:
      '\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    With the guidance of your own, personal mentor you’ll work in a variety of\r\n    different open source code projects. This role can be tailored according to\r\n    your wishes and you’ll have the chance to impact on what kind of projects\r\n    you wish to contribute in. This year’s projects have involved for example:\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cul\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Creating open source services for public administrations using Django\r\n        and React\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Building an underwater information system for divers with React.js,\r\n        Leaflet, LESS and Webpack technologies\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n    \u003cli\u003e\r\n        Building a modern Django based web platform and a Magento based\r\n        web-shop and making integrations to third party systems with .NET\r\n        \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003c/li\u003e\r\n\u003c/ul\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    We hope that you’ve already gained some skills in programming, preferably\r\n    in Python and JavaScript, either via studies, work or own projects.\r\n    Experience with frameworks such as Django, React and Angular are highly\r\n    appreciated.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n    What we value the most is a good attitude and the desire to grow as a\r\n    developer. You confront new challenges with an open mind and you’re not\r\n    afraid of taking initiative. Group work comes naturally to you and you\r\n    enjoy working in client projects. You communicate fluently in English.\r\n    Finnish skills are seen as an advantage.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    “I’ve had it with these mothaf*ckin’ snakes in this mothaf*ckin’ office!”\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    You’ll never hear that sentence at Anders. Mainly because baby snakes and\r\n    grown up snakes in Anders are their greatest asset and the company looks\r\n    after them. In 2017 Anders was listed in the Great Place to Work ranking as\r\n    the 5th best in Finland. The success comes from a mutual respect where\r\n    employees get support in their professional development and they get to be\r\n    a part of developing the company. We want to encourage our employees to\r\n    deepen their knowledge in programming so we provide internal educations and\r\n    the chance to study topics that interest you a few hours a week during work\r\n    times.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    So you want to slither in?\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    Please send your CV and application in pdf form here\r\n    \u003ca\r\n        href="https://apply.atalent.fi/anders-junior-python-developer-10-2018"\r\n        target="_blank"\r\n        rel="noopener noreferrer"\r\n    \u003e\r\n        https://apply.atalent.fi/anders-junior-python-developer-10-2018\r\n    \u003c/a\u003e\r\n    no later than October 25th. Also attach your GitHub profile or other\r\n    relevat working samples. We will interview and invite the top 10 potential\r\n    baby snakes to Anders’ snake nest in Helsinki where you will get to hang\r\n    out with Anders’ staff and learn cool IoT stuffs.\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    The event will be held on Wednesday 7th of November so clear your calendar\r\n    for that afternoon. By joining us at the event you’ll have the chance to\r\n    talk with your possible future colleagues and learn about IoT. Anders is a\r\n    good host and will offer snacks and beverages to participants. After the\r\n    event, the process continues with Anders’ own code test and interviews.\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e',
