    description:
      "\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003ch2\u003eUniversity of Helsinki\u003c/h2\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    Summer Trainee / Project Researcher (Bioinformatics)\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    Technological development has enabled resolving the genomes of individuals\r\n    without a reference. Combined with high-throughput DNA sequencing, the\r\n    latest findings have questioned the basic principles of DNA mutation\r\n    processes and revealed a novel mechanism, capable of both causing complex\r\n    mutation patterns and creating perfect inverted repeat sequences.\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    The aim of our Academy-funded research project is to understand the\r\n    Template Switch Mutation mechanism using high-throughput sequencing data.\r\n    Your role is to develop methods for retrieval and processing of raw data,\r\n    identification of complex mutation patterns, and analysis of the underlying\r\n    mutation mechanism. The work requires fluency with Linux command-line work\r\n    and scripting. Experience in bioinformatics and C++ is seen as a benefit.\r\n    The work can be done fully remotely.\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    \u003cbr/\u003e\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n\u003cdiv\u003e\r\n    To apply for the position or to ask for more details, please contact Ari\r\n    Löytynoja at ari.loytynoja@helsinki.fi. Application deadline is 31.5.2021\r\n    but it may be filled before that.\r\n\u003c/div\u003e\r\n",
